  5   /**
  6    * ML.Analytics collects data of user actions and analytics it in MaxLeap.
  7    * @param {Object} options The initial configuration
  8    * @constructor
  9    */
 10   ML.Analytics = function(options){
 11     var UUID = uuid.v4();
 12     var UNKNOWN = this.UNKNOWN = '0,0';
 13     var INSTALLATION_FLAG = 'ml_installation_flag';
 14     var REFERRER_START = '8cf1f64d97224f6eba3867b57822f528';
 15     var detector = new ML.Detector();
 16 
 17     var installation = ML.store.get(INSTALLATION_FLAG);
 18     if(!installation){
 19       installation = uuid.v4();
 20     }
 21     this.options = _.extend({
 22       sdkVersion: ML.VERSION,
 23       appUserId: installation,
 24       sessionId: UUID,
 25       deviceId: installation,
 26       duration: 0,
 27       push: false,
 28       upgrade: false,
 29       url: window.location.href,
 30       referer: document.referrer || REFERRER_START,
 31       userAgent: window.navigator.userAgent,
 32       os: 'web',
 33       osVersion: detector.getOSName() + ' ' + detector.getOSVersion(),
 34       resolution: detector.getResolution(),
 35       language: detector.getLanguage(),
 36       userCreateTime: new Date().getTime(),
 37       startTime: new Date().getTime(),
 38       ctimestamp: new Date().getTime(),
 39       channel: UNKNOWN,
 40       network: UNKNOWN,
 41       carrier: UNKNOWN,
 42       national: UNKNOWN,
 43       deviceModel: UNKNOWN
 44     }, options);
 45 
 46     this.trackPageBegin();
 47     //Track new user only one time.
 48     if(!ML.store.get(INSTALLATION_FLAG)){
 49       this._trackNewUser();
 50     }
 51     
 52     if(!ML.store.get(INSTALLATION_FLAG)){
 53       ML.store.set(INSTALLATION_FLAG, installation, { expires: '1Y' });
 54     }

214   _.extend(ML.Analytics, /** @lends ML.Analytics */{
215     /**
216      * Post data to server, and retry when fail.
217      * @param {Object} data
218      * @param {i} i Retry time, by default undefined.
219      * @returns {Promise}
220      * @private
221      */
222     _request: function(data, headers, options, i){
223       options = options || {};
224       if(!ML.analyticsEnable){
225         return;
226       }
227 
228       var url = options.url || '2.0/analytics/at';
229       var method = options.method || 'POST';
230 
231       return ML._ajax(method, ML.serverURL + url, JSON.stringify(data), null, null, {
232         'Content-Type': 'application/json',
233         'X-ML-Appid': headers.appId
234       }).then(function(res){
235         return res;
236       }, function(res){
237         i = i || 0;
238         if(i < 2){
239           ML.Analytics._request(data, headers, options, ++i);
240         }
241         return res;
242       });
243     }
244   })

294   _.extend(ML.Detector.prototype, {
295     getOSName: function () {
296       return this.detector.os.name === 'na' ? 'unknown' : this.detector.os.name;
297     },
298     getOSVersion: function () {
299       //如果是windows系统,web-detector返回的是NT的版本号,需要转换成windows版本
300       if(this.detector.os.name === 'windows'){
301         if (this.detector.os.version >= 10) {
302           return '10';
303         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 6.3) {
304           return '8.1';
305         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 6.2) {
306           return '8';
307         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 6.1) {
308           return '7';
309         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 6.0) {
310           return 'vista';
311         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 5.1) {
312           return 'xp';
313         } else if (this.detector.os.version >= 5.0) {
314           return '2000';
315         }
316       }
317       return this.detector.os.fullVersion === '-1' ? 'unknown' : this.detector.os.fullVersion;
318     },
319     getResolution: function () {
320       return screen.width + '*' + screen.height
321     },
322     getLanguage: function () {
323       return (navigator.language || navigator.userLanguage).match(/\w+(?=-)/)[0];
324     }
325   });

683 },{"underscore":23}],5:[function(require,module,exports){
684 /*global _: false */
685 module.exports = function(ML) {
686   var eventSplitter = /\s+/;
687   var slice = Array.prototype.slice;
688 
689   /**
690    * <p>ML.Events is a fork of Backbone's Events module, provided for your
691    * convenience.</p>
692    *
693    * <p>A module that can be mixed in to any object in order to provide
694    * it with custom events. You may bind callback functions to an event
695    * with `on`, or remove these functions with `off`.
696    * Triggering an event fires all callbacks in the order that `on` was
697    * called.
698    *
699    * <pre>
700    *     var object = {};
701    *     _.extend(object, ML.Events);
702    *     object.on('expand', function(){ alert('expanded'); });
703    *     object.trigger('expand');</pre></p>
704    *
705    * <p>For more information, see the
706    * <a href="http://documentcloud.github.com/backbone/#Events">Backbone
707    * documentation</a>.</p>
708    */
709   ML.Events = {
710     /**
711      * Bind one or more space separated events, `events`, to a `callback`
712      * function. Passing `"all"` will bind the callback to all events fired.
713      */
714     on: function(events, callback, context) {
715 
716       var calls, event, node, tail, list;
717       if (!callback) {
718         return this;
719       }
720       events = events.split(eventSplitter);
721       calls = this._callbacks || (this._callbacks = {});
722 
723       // Create an immutable callback list, allowing traversal during
724       // modification.  The tail is an empty object that will always be used
725       // as the next node.
726       event = events.shift();
727       while (event) {
728         list = calls[event];
729         node = list ? list.tail : {};
730         node.next = tail = {};
731         node.context = context;
732         node.callback = callback;
733         calls[event] = {tail: tail, next: list ? list.next : node};
734         event = events.shift();
735       }
736 
737       return this;
738     },
739 
740     /**
741      * Remove one or many callbacks. If `context` is null, removes all callbacks
742      * with that function. If `callback` is null, removes all callbacks for the
743      * event. If `events` is null, removes all bound callbacks for all events.
744      */
745     off: function(events, callback, context) {
746       var event, calls, node, tail, cb, ctx;
747 
748       // No events, or removing *all* events.
749       if (!(calls = this._callbacks)) {
750         return;
751       }
752       if (!(events || callback || context)) {
753         delete this._callbacks;
754         return this;
755       }
756 
757       // Loop through the listed events and contexts, splicing them out of the
758       // linked list of callbacks if appropriate.
759       events = events ? events.split(eventSplitter) : _.keys(calls);
760       event = events.shift();
761       while (event) {
762         node = calls[event];
763         delete calls[event];
764         if (!node || !(callback || context)) {
765           continue;
766         }
767         // Create a new list, omitting the indicated callbacks.
768         tail = node.tail;
769         node = node.next;
770         while (node !== tail) {
771           cb = node.callback;
772           ctx = node.context;
773           if ((callback && cb !== callback) || (context && ctx !== context)) {
774             this.on(event, cb, ctx);
775           }
776           node = node.next;
777         }
778         event = events.shift();
779       }
780 
781       return this;
782     },
783 
784     /**
785      * Trigger one or many events, firing all bound callbacks. Callbacks are
786      * passed the same arguments as `trigger` is, apart from the event name
787      * (unless you're listening on `"all"`, which will cause your callback to
788      * receive the true name of the event as the first argument).
789      */
790     trigger: function(events) {
791       var event, node, calls, tail, args, all, rest;
792       if (!(calls = this._callbacks)) {
793         return this;
794       }
795       all = calls.all;
796       events = events.split(eventSplitter);
797       rest = slice.call(arguments, 1);
798 
799       // For each event, walk through the linked list of callbacks twice,
800       // first to trigger the event, then to trigger any `"all"` callbacks.
801       event = events.shift();
802       while (event) {
803         node = calls[event];
804         if (node) {
805           tail = node.tail;
806           while ((node = node.next) !== tail) {
807             node.callback.apply(node.context || this, rest);
808           }
809         }
810         node = all;
811         if (node) {
812           tail = node.tail;
813           args = [event].concat(rest);
814           while ((node = node.next) !== tail) {
815             node.callback.apply(node.context || this, args);
816           }
817         }
818         event = events.shift();
819       }
820 
821       return this;
822     }
823   };
824 
825   /**
826    * @function
827    */
828   ML.Events.bind = ML.Events.on;
829 
830   /**
831    * @function
832    */
833   ML.Events.unbind = ML.Events.off;
834 };

892   /**
893    * A ML.File is a local representation of a file that is saved to the ML cloud.
894    * @param {String} name The file's name.
895    * @param {Array} data The data for the file, as either:
896    *     1. an Object like { base64: "..." } with a base64-encoded String.
897    *     2. an Object url.
898    * @class
899    */
900   ML.File = function (name, data) {
901     this._name = name;
902     this._source = new ML.Promise(function (resolve) {
903       resolve(data);
904     })
905   };

930      * @return {Promise} Promise that is resolved when the save finishes.
931      */
932     save: function () {

934       return this._source.then(function (source) {
935         return ML._request('files', self._name, null, 'PUT', source).then(function (res) {
936           self._name = res.name;
937           self._url = res.url;
938           return self;
939         });

941     },

945      * @return {Promise} Promise that is resolved when the destroy finishes.
946      */
947     destroy: function () {
948       return ML._request('files', null, null, 'DELETE', null, {'X-LAS-Fid': this._name});

956 /*global navigator: false */
957 module.exports = function(ML) {
958   /**
959    * Creates a new GeoPoint with any of the following forms:<br>
960    *   <pre>
961    *   new GeoPoint(otherGeoPoint)
962    *   new GeoPoint(30, 30)
963    *   new GeoPoint([30, 30])
964    *   new GeoPoint({latitude: 30, longitude: 30})
965    *   new GeoPoint()  // defaults to (0, 0)
966    *   </pre>
967    * @class
968    *
969    * <p>Represents a latitude / longitude point that may be associated
970    * with a key in a MLObject or used as a reference point for geo queries.
971    * This allows proximity-based queries on the key.</p>
972    *
973    * <p>Only one key in a class may contain a GeoPoint.</p>
974    *
975    * <p>Example:<pre>
976    *   var point = new ML.GeoPoint(30.0, -20.0);
977    *   var object = new ML.Object("PlaceObject");
978    *   object.set("location", point);
979    *   object.save();</pre></p>
980    */
981   ML.GeoPoint = function(arg1, arg2) {
982     if (_.isArray(arg1)) {
983       ML.GeoPoint._validate(arg1[0], arg1[1]);
984       this.latitude = arg1[0];
985       this.longitude = arg1[1];
986     } else if (_.isObject(arg1)) {
987       ML.GeoPoint._validate(arg1.latitude, arg1.longitude);
988       this.latitude = arg1.latitude;
989       this.longitude = arg1.longitude;
990     } else if (_.isNumber(arg1) && _.isNumber(arg2)) {
991       ML.GeoPoint._validate(arg1, arg2);
992       this.latitude = arg1;
993       this.longitude = arg2;
994     } else {
995       this.latitude = 0;
996       this.longitude = 0;
997     }
998 
999     // Add properties so that anyone using Webkit or Mozilla will get an error
1000     // if they try to set values that are out of bounds.
1001     var self = this;
1002     if (this.__defineGetter__ && this.__defineSetter__) {
1003       // Use _latitude and _longitude to actually store the values, and add
1004       // getters and setters for latitude and longitude.
1005       this._latitude = this.latitude;
1006       this._longitude = this.longitude;
1007       this.__defineGetter__("latitude", function() {
1008         return self._latitude;
1009       });
1010       this.__defineGetter__("longitude", function() {
1011         return self._longitude;
1012       });
1013       this.__defineSetter__("latitude", function(val) {
1014         ML.GeoPoint._validate(val, self.longitude);
1015         self._latitude = val;
1016       });
1017       this.__defineSetter__("longitude", function(val) {
1018         ML.GeoPoint._validate(self.latitude, val);
1019         self._longitude = val;
1020       });
1021     }
1022   };
1023 
1024   /**
1025    * @lends ML.GeoPoint.prototype
1026    * @property {float} latitude North-south portion of the coordinate, in range
1027    *   [-90, 90].  Throws an exception if set out of range in a modern browser.
1028    * @property {float} longitude East-west portion of the coordinate, in range
1029    *   [-180, 180].  Throws if set out of range in a modern browser.
1030    */
1031 
1032   /**
1033    * Throws an exception if the given lat-long is out of bounds.
1034    */
1035   ML.GeoPoint._validate = function(latitude, longitude) {
1036     if (latitude < -90.0) {
1037       throw "ML.GeoPoint latitude " + latitude + " < -90.0.";
1038     }
1039     if (latitude > 90.0) {
1040       throw "ML.GeoPoint latitude " + latitude + " > 90.0.";
1041     }
1042     if (longitude < -180.0) {
1043       throw "ML.GeoPoint longitude " + longitude + " < -180.0.";
1044     }
1045     if (longitude > 180.0) {
1046       throw "ML.GeoPoint longitude " + longitude + " > 180.0.";
1047     }
1048   };
1049 
1050   /**
1051    * Creates a GeoPoint with the user's current location, if available.
1052    * Calls options.success with a new GeoPoint instance or calls options.error.
1053    * @param {Object} options An object with success and error callbacks.
1054    */
1055   ML.GeoPoint.current = function(options) {
1056     var promise = new ML.Promise();
1057     navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(function(location) {
1058       promise.resolve(new ML.GeoPoint({
1059         latitude: location.coords.latitude,
1060         longitude: location.coords.longitude
1061       }));
1062 
1063     }, function(error) {
1064       promise.reject(error);
1065     });
1066 
1067     return promise._thenRunCallbacks(options);
1068   };
1069 
1070   ML.GeoPoint.prototype = {
1071     /**
1072      * Returns a JSON representation of the GeoPoint, suitable for ML.
1073      * @return {Object}
1074      */
1075     toJSON: function() {
1076       ML.GeoPoint._validate(this.latitude, this.longitude);
1077       return {
1078         "__type": "GeoPoint",
1079         latitude: this.latitude,
1080         longitude: this.longitude
1081       };
1082     },
1083 
1084     /**
1085      * Returns the distance from this GeoPoint to another in radians.
1086      * @param {ML.GeoPoint} point the other ML.GeoPoint.
1087      * @return {Number}
1088      */
1089     radiansTo: function(point) {
1090       var d2r = Math.PI / 180.0;
1091       var lat1rad = this.latitude * d2r;
1092       var long1rad = this.longitude * d2r;
1093       var lat2rad = point.latitude * d2r;
1094       var long2rad = point.longitude * d2r;
1095       var deltaLat = lat1rad - lat2rad;
1096       var deltaLong = long1rad - long2rad;
1097       var sinDeltaLatDiv2 = Math.sin(deltaLat / 2);
1098       var sinDeltaLongDiv2 = Math.sin(deltaLong / 2);
1099       // Square of half the straight line chord distance between both points.
1100       var a = ((sinDeltaLatDiv2 * sinDeltaLatDiv2) +
1101                (Math.cos(lat1rad) * Math.cos(lat2rad) *
1102                 sinDeltaLongDiv2 * sinDeltaLongDiv2));
1103       a = Math.min(1.0, a);
1104       return 2 * Math.asin(Math.sqrt(a));
1105     },
1106 
1107     /**
1108      * Returns the distance from this GeoPoint to another in kilometers.
1109      * @param {ML.GeoPoint} point the other ML.GeoPoint.
1110      * @return {Number}
1111      */
1112     kilometersTo: function(point) {
1113       return this.radiansTo(point) * 6371.0;
1114     },
1115 
1116     /**
1117      * Returns the distance from this GeoPoint to another in miles.
1118      * @param {ML.GeoPoint} point the other ML.GeoPoint.
1119      * @return {Number}
1120      */
1121     milesTo: function(point) {
1122       return this.radiansTo(point) * 3958.8;
1123     }
1124   };
1125 };

1132 // ML.Object is analogous to the Java MLObject.
1133 // It also implements the same interface as a Backbone model.
1134 
1135 module.exports = function (ML) {
1136   /**
1137    * Creates a new model with defined attributes. A client id (cid) is
1138    * automatically generated and assigned for you.
1139    *
1140    * <p>You won't normally call this method directly.  It is recommended that
1141    * you use a subclass of <code>ML.Object</code> instead, created by calling
1142    * <code>extend</code>.</p>
1143    *
1144    * <p>However, if you don't want to use a subclass, or aren't sure which
1145    * subclass is appropriate, you can use this form:<pre>
1146    *     var object = new ML.Object("ClassName");
1147    * </pre>
1148    * That is basically equivalent to:<pre>
1149    *     var MyClass = ML.Object.extend("ClassName");
1150    *     var object = new MyClass();
1151    * </pre></p>
1152    *
1153    * @param {Object} attributes The initial set of data to store in the object.
1154    * @param {Object} options A set of Backbone-like options for creating the
1155    *     object.  The only option currently supported is "collection".
1156    * @see ML.Object.extend
1157    *
1158    * @class
1159    *
1160    * <p>The fundamental unit of ML data, which implements the Backbone Model
1161    * interface.</p>
1162    */
1163   ML.Object = function (attributes, options) {
1164     // Allow new ML.Object("ClassName") as a shortcut to _create.
1165     if (_.isString(attributes)) {
1166       return ML.Object._create.apply(this, arguments);
1167     }
1168 
1169     attributes = attributes || {};
1170     if (options && options.parse) {
1171       attributes = this.parse(attributes);
1172     }
1173     var defaults = ML._getValue(this, 'defaults');
1174     if (defaults) {
1175       attributes = _.extend({}, defaults, attributes);
1176     }
1177     if (options && options.collection) {
1178       this.collection = options.collection;
1179     }
1180 
1181     this._serverData = {};  // The last known data for this object from cloud.
1182     this._opSetQueue = [{}];  // List of sets of changes to the data.
1183     this.attributes = {};  // The best estimate of this's current data.
1184 
1185     this._hashedJSON = {};  // Hash of values of containers at last save.
1186     this._escapedAttributes = {};
1187     this.cid = _.uniqueId('c');
1188     this.changed = {};
1189     this._silent = {};
1190     this._pending = {};
1191     if (!this.set(attributes, {silent: true})) {
1192       throw new Error("Can't create an invalid ML.Object");
1193     }
1194     this.changed = {};
1195     this._silent = {};
1196     this._pending = {};
1197     this._hasData = true;
1198     this._previousAttributes = _.clone(this.attributes);
1199     this.initialize.apply(this, arguments);
1200   };

1207   /**

1209    * If any error is encountered, stops and calls the error handler.
1210    * There are two ways you can call this function.
1211    *
1212    * The Backbone way:<pre>
1213    *   ML.Object.saveAll([object1, object2, ...], {
1214    *     success: function(list) {
1215    *       // All the objects were saved.
1216    *     },
1217    *     error: function(error) {
1218    *       // An error occurred while saving one of the objects.
1219    *     },
1220    *   });
1221    * </pre>
1222    * A simplified syntax:<pre>
1223    *   ML.Object.saveAll([object1, object2, ...], function(list, error) {
1224    *     if (list) {
1225    *       // All the objects were saved.
1226    *     } else {
1227    *       // An error occurred.
1228    *     }
1229    *   });
1230    * </pre>
1231    *
1232    * @param {Array} list A list of <code>ML.Object</code>.
1233    * @param {Object} options A Backbone-style callback object.
1234    */
1235   ML.Object.saveAll = function (list, options) {
1236     return ML.Object._deepSaveAsync(list)._thenRunCallbacks(options);

1291        * @return {Object}

1304         ML._objectEach(json, function (val, key) {
1305           json[key] = ML._encode(val, seenObjects);

1325           } else {
1326             json.updatedAt = this.updatedAt;

1334       /**
1335        * Updates _hashedJSON to reflect the current state of this object.
1336        * Adds any changed hash values to the set of pending changes.
1337        */
1338       _refreshCache: function () {
1339         var self = this;
1340         if (self._refreshingCache) {
1341           return;
1342         }
1343         self._refreshingCache = true;
1344         ML._objectEach(this.attributes, function (value, key) {
1345           if (value instanceof ML.Object) {
1346             value._refreshCache();
1347           } else if (_.isObject(value)) {
1348             if (self._resetCacheForKey(key)) {
1349               self.set(key, new ML.Op.Set(value), {silent: true});
1350             }
1351           }

1360        * @param {String} attr An attribute name (optional).
1361        * @return {Boolean}

1363       dirty: function (attr) {
1364         this._refreshCache();
1365

1369           return (currentChanges[attr] ? true : false);
1370         }

1372           return true;
1373         }

1375           return true;

1410             throw "Called relation() on non-relation field " + attr;
1411           }

1413           return value;

1430           escaped = '';
1431         } else {

1448       /**
1449        * Pulls "special" fields like objectId, createdAt, etc. out of attrs
1450        * and puts them on "this" directly.  Removes them from attrs.
1451        * @param attrs - A dictionary with the data for this ML.Object.
1452        */
1453       _mergeMagicFields: function (attrs) {
1454         // Check for changes of magic fields.
1455         var model = this;
1456         var specialFields = ["id", "objectId", "createdAt", "updatedAt"];
1457         ML._arrayEach(specialFields, function (attr) {
1458           if (attrs[attr]) {
1459             if (attr === "objectId") {
1460               model.id = attrs[attr];
1461             } else if ((attr === "createdAt" || attr === "updatedAt") && !_.isDate(attrs[attr])) {
1462               model[attr] = ML._parseDate(attrs[attr]);
1463             } else {
1464               model[attr] = attrs[attr];
1465             }
1466             delete attrs[attr];
1467           }
1468         });

1478       /**
1479        * Called when a save fails because of an error. Any changes that were part
1480        * of the save need to be merged with changes made after the save. This
1481        * might throw an exception is you do conflicting operations. For example,
1482        * if you do:
1483        *   object.set("foo", "bar");
1484        *   object.set("invalid field name", "baz");
1485        *   object.save();
1486        *   object.increment("foo");
1487        * then this will throw when the save fails and the client tries to merge
1488        * "bar" with the +1.
1489        */
1490       _cancelSave: function () {
1491         var self = this;
1492         var failedChanges = _.first(this._opSetQueue);
1493         this._opSetQueue = _.rest(this._opSetQueue);
1494         var nextChanges = _.first(this._opSetQueue);
1495         ML._objectEach(failedChanges, function (op, key) {
1496           var op1 = failedChanges[key];
1497           var op2 = nextChanges[key];
1498           if (op1 && op2) {
1499             nextChanges[key] = op2._mergeWithPrevious(op1);
1500           } else if (op1) {
1501             nextChanges[key] = op1;
1502           }
1503         });
1504         this._saving = this._saving - 1;
1505       },
1506 
1507       /**
1508        * Called when a save completes successfully. This merges the changes that
1509        * were saved into the known server data, and overrides it with any data
1510        * sent directly from the server.
1511        */
1512       _finishSave: function (serverData) {
1513         // Grab a copy of any object referenced by this object. These instances
1514         // may have already been fetched, and we don't want to lose their data.
1515         // Note that doing it like this means we will unify separate copies of the
1516         // same object, but that's a risk we have to take.
1517         var fetchedObjects = {};
1518         ML._traverse(this.attributes, function (object) {
1519           if (object instanceof ML.Object && object.id && object._hasData) {
1520             fetchedObjects[object.id] = object;
1521           }
1522         });
1523 
1524         var savedChanges = _.first(this._opSetQueue);
1525         this._opSetQueue = _.rest(this._opSetQueue);
1526         this._applyOpSet(savedChanges, this._serverData);
1527         this._mergeMagicFields(serverData);
1528         var self = this;
1529         ML._objectEach(serverData, function (value, key) {
1530           self._serverData[key] = ML._decode(key, value);
1531 
1532           // Look for any objects that might have become unfetched and fix them
1533           // by replacing their values with the previously observed values.
1534           var fetched = ML._traverse(self._serverData[key], function (object) {
1535             if (object instanceof ML.Object && fetchedObjects[object.id]) {
1536               return fetchedObjects[object.id];
1537             }
1538           });
1539           if (fetched) {
1540             self._serverData[key] = fetched;
1541           }
1542         });
1543         this._rebuildAllEstimatedData();
1544         this._saving = this._saving - 1;
1545       },
1546 
1547       /**
1548        * Called when a fetch or login is complete to set the known server data to
1549        * the given object.
1550        */
1551       _finishFetch: function (serverData, hasData) {
1552         // Clear out any changes the user might have made previously.
1553         this._opSetQueue = [{}];
1554 
1555         // Bring in all the new server data.
1556         this._mergeMagicFields(serverData);
1557         var self = this;
1558         ML._objectEach(serverData, function (value, key) {
1559           self._serverData[key] = ML._decode(key, value);
1560         });
1561 
1562         // Refresh the attributes.
1563         this._rebuildAllEstimatedData();
1564 
1565         // Clear out the cache of mutable containers.
1566         this._refreshCache();
1567         this._opSetQueue = [{}];
1568 
1569         this._hasData = hasData;
1570       },
1571 
1572       /**
1573        * Applies the set of ML.Op in opSet to the object target.
1574        */
1575       _applyOpSet: function (opSet, target) {
1576         var self = this;
1577         ML._objectEach(opSet, function (change, key) {
1578           target[key] = change._estimate(target[key], self, key);
1579           if (target[key] === ML.Op._UNSET) {
1580             delete target[key];
1581           }
1582         });
1583       },
1584 
1585       /**
1586        * Replaces the cached value for key with the current value.
1587        * Returns true if the new value is different than the old value.
1588        */
1589       _resetCacheForKey: function (key) {
1590         var value = this.attributes[key];
1591         if (_.isObject(value) && !(value instanceof ML.Object) && !(value instanceof ML.File)) {
1592 
1593           value = value.toJSON ? value.toJSON() : value;
1594           var json = JSON.stringify(value);
1595           if (this._hashedJSON[key] !== json) {
1596             var wasSet = !!this._hashedJSON[key];
1597             this._hashedJSON[key] = json;
1598             return wasSet;
1599           }
1600         }
1601         return false;
1602       },
1603 
1604       /**
1605        * Populates attributes[key] by starting with the last known data from the
1606        * server, and applying all of the local changes that have been made to that
1607        * key since then.
1608        */
1609       _rebuildEstimatedDataForKey: function (key) {
1610         var self = this;
1611         delete this.attributes[key];
1612         if (this._serverData[key]) {
1613           this.attributes[key] = this._serverData[key];
1614         }
1615         ML._arrayEach(this._opSetQueue, function (opSet) {
1616           var op = opSet[key];
1617           if (op) {
1618             self.attributes[key] = op._estimate(self.attributes[key], self, key);
1619             if (self.attributes[key] === ML.Op._UNSET) {
1620               delete self.attributes[key];
1621             } else {
1622               self._resetCacheForKey(key);
1623             }
1624           }
1625         });
1626       },
1627 
1628       /**
1629        * Populates attributes by starting with the last known data from the
1630        * server, and applying all of the local changes that have been made since
1631        * then.
1632        */
1633       _rebuildAllEstimatedData: function () {
1634         var self = this;
1635 
1636         var previousAttributes = _.clone(this.attributes);
1637 
1638         this.attributes = _.clone(this._serverData);
1639         ML._arrayEach(this._opSetQueue, function (opSet) {
1640           self._applyOpSet(opSet, self.attributes);
1641           ML._objectEach(opSet, function (op, key) {
1642             self._resetCacheForKey(key);
1643           });
1644         });
1645 
1646         // Trigger change events for anything that changed because of the fetch.
1647         ML._objectEach(previousAttributes, function (oldValue, key) {
1648           if (self.attributes[key] !== oldValue) {
1649             self.trigger('change:' + key, self, self.attributes[key], {});
1650           }
1651         });
1652         ML._objectEach(this.attributes, function (newValue, key) {
1653           if (!_.has(previousAttributes, key)) {
1654             self.trigger('change:' + key, self, newValue, {});
1655           }
1656         });
1657       },
1658 
1659       /**
1660        * Sets a hash of model attributes on the object, firing
1661        * <code>"change"</code> unless you choose to silence it.
1662        *
1663        * <p>You can call it with an object containing keys and values, or with one
1664        * key and value.  For example:<pre>
1665        *   gameTurn.set({
1666      *     player: player1,
1667      *     diceRoll: 2
1668      *   }, {
1669      *     error: function(gameTurnAgain, error) {
1670      *       // The set failed validation.
1671      *     }
1672      *   });
1673        *
1674        *   game.set("currentPlayer", player2, {
1675      *     error: function(gameTurnAgain, error) {
1676      *       // The set failed validation.
1677      *     }
1678      *   });
1679        *
1680        *   game.set("finished", true);</pre></p>
1681        *
1682        * @param {String} key The key to set.
1683        * @param {} value The value to give it.
1684        * @param {Object} options A set of Backbone-like options for the set.
1685        *     The only supported options are <code>silent</code>,
1686        *     <code>error</code>, and <code>promise</code>.
1687        * @return {Boolean} true if the set succeeded.
1688        * @see ML.Object#validate
1689        * @see ML.Error
1690        */
1691       set: function (key, value, options) {
1692         var attrs, attr;
1693         if (_.isObject(key) || ML._isNullOrUndefined(key)) {
1694           attrs = key;
1695           ML._objectEach(attrs, function (v, k) {
1696             attrs[k] = ML._decode(k, v);
1697           });
1698           options = value;
1699         } else {
1700           attrs = {};
1701           attrs[key] = ML._decode(key, value);
1702         }
1703 
1704         // Extract attributes and options.
1705         options = options || {};
1706         if (!attrs) {
1707           return this;
1708         }
1709         if (attrs instanceof ML.Object) {
1710           attrs = attrs.attributes;
1711         }
1712 
1713         // If the unset option is used, every attribute should be a Unset.
1714         if (options.unset) {
1715           ML._objectEach(attrs, function (unused_value, key) {
1716             attrs[key] = new ML.Op.Unset();
1717           });
1718         }
1719 
1720         // Apply all the attributes to get the estimated values.
1721         var dataToValidate = _.clone(attrs);
1722         var self = this;
1723         ML._objectEach(dataToValidate, function (value, key) {
1724           if (value instanceof ML.Op) {
1725             dataToValidate[key] = value._estimate(self.attributes[key],
1726               self, key);
1727             if (dataToValidate[key] === ML.Op._UNSET) {
1728               delete dataToValidate[key];
1729             }
1730           }
1731         });
1732 
1733         // Run validation.
1734         if (!this._validate(attrs, options)) {
1735           return false;
1736         }
1737 
1738         this._mergeMagicFields(attrs);
1739 
1740         options.changes = {};
1741         var escaped = this._escapedAttributes;
1742         var prev = this._previousAttributes || {};
1743 
1744         // Update attributes.
1745         ML._arrayEach(_.keys(attrs), function (attr) {
1746           var val = attrs[attr];
1747 
1748           // If this is a relation object we need to set the parent correctly,
1749           // since the location where it was parsed does not have access to
1750           // this object.
1751           if (val instanceof ML.Relation) {
1752             val.parent = self;
1753           }
1754 
1755           if (!(val instanceof ML.Op)) {
1756             val = new ML.Op.Set(val);
1757           }
1758 
1759           // See if this change will actually have any effect.
1760           var isRealChange = true;
1761           if (val instanceof ML.Op.Set &&
1762             _.isEqual(self.attributes[attr], val.value)) {
1763             isRealChange = false;
1764           }
1765 
1766           if (isRealChange) {
1767             delete escaped[attr];
1768             if (options.silent) {
1769               self._silent[attr] = true;
1770             } else {
1771               options.changes[attr] = true;
1772             }
1773           }
1774 
1775           var currentChanges = _.last(self._opSetQueue);
1776           currentChanges[attr] = val._mergeWithPrevious(currentChanges[attr]);
1777           self._rebuildEstimatedDataForKey(attr);
1778 
1779           if (isRealChange) {
1780             self.changed[attr] = self.attributes[attr];
1781             if (!options.silent) {
1782               self._pending[attr] = true;
1783             }
1784           } else {
1785             delete self.changed[attr];
1786             delete self._pending[attr];
1787           }
1788         });
1789 
1790         if (!options.silent) {
1791           this.change(options);
1792         }
1793         return this;
1794       },
1795 
1796       /**
1797        * Remove an attribute from the model, firing <code>"change"</code> unless
1798        * you choose to silence it. This is a noop if the attribute doesn't
1799        * exist.
1800        */
1801       unset: function (attr, options) {
1802         options = options || {};
1803         options.unset = true;
1804         return this.set(attr, null, options);
1805       },
1806 
1807       /**
1808        * Atomically increments the value of the given attribute the next time the
1809        * object is saved. If no amount is specified, 1 is used by default.
1810        *
1811        * @param attr {String} The key.
1812        * @param amount {Number} The amount to increment by.
1813        */
1814       increment: function (attr, amount) {
1815         if (_.isUndefined(amount) || _.isNull(amount)) {
1816           amount = 1;
1817         }
1818         return this.set(attr, new ML.Op.Increment(amount));
1819       },
1820 
1821       /**
1822        * Atomically add an object to the end of the array associated with a given
1823        * key.
1824        * @param attr {String} The key.
1825        * @param item {} The item to add.
1826        */
1827       add: function (attr, item) {
1828         return this.set(attr, new ML.Op.Add([item]));
1829       },
1830 
1831       /**
1832        * Atomically add an object to the array associated with a given key, only
1833        * if it is not already present in the array. The position of the insert is
1834        * not guaranteed.
1835        *
1836        * @param attr {String} The key.
1837        * @param item {} The object to add.
1838        */
1839       addUnique: function (attr, item) {
1840         return this.set(attr, new ML.Op.AddUnique([item]));
1841       },
1842 
1843       /**
1844        * Atomically remove all instances of an object from the array associated
1845        * with a given key.
1846        *
1847        * @param attr {String} The key.
1848        * @param item {} The object to remove.
1849        */
1850       remove: function (attr, item) {
1851         return this.set(attr, new ML.Op.Remove([item]));
1852       },
1853 
1854       /**
1855        * Returns an instance of a subclass of ML.Op describing what kind of
1856        * modification has been performed on this field since the last time it was
1857        * saved. For example, after calling object.increment("x"), calling
1858        * object.op("x") would return an instance of ML.Op.Increment.
1859        *
1860        * @param attr {String} The key.
1861        * @returns {ML.Op} The operation, or undefined if none.
1862        */
1863       op: function (attr) {
1864         return _.last(this._opSetQueue)[attr];
1865       },
1866 
1867       /**
1868        * Clear all attributes on the model, firing <code>"change"</code> unless
1869        * you choose to silence it.
1870        */
1871       clear: function (options) {
1872         options = options || {};
1873         options.unset = true;
1874         var keysToClear = _.extend(this.attributes, this._operations);
1875         return this.set(keysToClear, options);
1876       },
1877 
1878       /**
1879        * Returns a JSON-encoded set of operations to be sent with the next save
1880        * request.
1881        */
1882       _getSaveJSON: function () {
1883         var json = _.clone(_.first(this._opSetQueue));
1884         ML._objectEach(json, function (op, key) {
1885           json[key] = op.toJSON();
1886         });
1887         return json;
1888       },
1889 
1890       /**
1891        * Returns true if this object can be serialized for saving.
1892        */
1893       _canBeSerialized: function () {
1894         return ML.Object._canBeSerializedAsValue(this.attributes);
1895       },
1896 
1897       /**
1898        * Fetch the model from the server. If the server's representation of the
1899        * model differs from its current attributes, they will be overriden,
1900        * triggering a <code>"change"</code> event.
1901        * @param {Object} fetchOptions Optional options to set 'keys' and
1902        *      'include' option.
1903        * @param {Object} options Optional Backbone-like options object to be
1904        *     passed in to set.
1905        * @return {ML.Promise} A promise that is fulfilled when the fetch
1906        *     completes.
1907        */
1908       fetch: function () {
1909         var options = null;
1910         var fetchOptions = {};
1911         if (arguments.length === 1) {
1912           options = arguments[0];
1913         } else if (arguments.length === 2) {
1914           fetchOptions = arguments[0];
1915           options = arguments[1];
1916         }
1917 
1918         var self = this;
1919         var request = ML._request("classes", this.className, this.id, 'GET',
1920           fetchOptions);
1921         return request.then(function (response, status, xhr) {
1922           self._finishFetch(self.parse(response, status, xhr), true);
1923           return self;
1924         })._thenRunCallbacks(options, this);
1925       },
1926 
1927       /**
1928        * Set a hash of model attributes, and save the model to the server.
1929        * updatedAt will be updated when the request returns.
1930        * You can either call it as:<pre>
1931        *   object.save();</pre>
1932        * or<pre>
1933        *   object.save(null, options);</pre>
1934        * or<pre>
1935        *   object.save(attrs, options);</pre>
1936        * or<pre>
1937        *   object.save(key, value, options);</pre>
1938        *
1939        * For example, <pre>
1940        *   gameTurn.save({
1941      *     player: "Jake Cutter",
1942      *     diceRoll: 2
1943      *   }, {
1944      *     success: function(gameTurnAgain) {
1945      *       // The save was successful.
1946      *     },
1947      *     error: function(gameTurnAgain, error) {
1948      *       // The save failed.  Error is an instance of ML.Error.
1949      *     }
1950      *   });</pre>
1951        * or with promises:<pre>
1952        *   gameTurn.save({
1953      *     player: "Jake Cutter",
1954      *     diceRoll: 2
1955      *   }).then(function(gameTurnAgain) {
1956      *     // The save was successful.
1957      *   }, function(error) {
1958      *     // The save failed.  Error is an instance of ML.Error.
1959      *   });</pre>
1960        *
1961        * @return {ML.Promise} A promise that is fulfilled when the save
1962        *     completes.
1963        * @see ML.Error
1964        */
1965       save: function (arg1, arg2, arg3) {
1966         var i, attrs, current, options, saved;
1967         if (_.isObject(arg1) || ML._isNullOrUndefined(arg1)) {
1968           attrs = arg1;
1969           options = arg2;
1970         } else {
1971           attrs = {};
1972           attrs[arg1] = arg2;
1973           options = arg3;
1974         }
1975 
1976         // Make save({ success: function() {} }) work.
1977         if (!options && attrs) {
1978           var extra_keys = _.reject(attrs, function (value, key) {
1979             return _.include(["success", "error", "wait"], key);
1980           });
1981           if (extra_keys.length === 0) {
1982             var all_functions = true;
1983             if (_.has(attrs, "success") && !_.isFunction(attrs.success)) {
1984               all_functions = false;
1985             }
1986             if (_.has(attrs, "error") && !_.isFunction(attrs.error)) {
1987               all_functions = false;
1988             }
1989             if (all_functions) {
1990               // This attrs object looks like it's really an options object,
1991               // and there's no other options object, so let's just use it.
1992               return this.save(null, attrs);
1993             }
1994           }
1995         }
1996 
1997         options = _.clone(options) || {};
1998         if (options.wait) {
1999           current = _.clone(this.attributes);
2000         }
2001 
2002         var setOptions = _.clone(options) || {};
2003         if (setOptions.wait) {
2004           setOptions.silent = true;
2005         }
2006         var setError;
2007         setOptions.error = function (model, error) {
2008           setError = error;
2009         };
2010         if (attrs && !this.set(attrs, setOptions)) {
2011           return ML.Promise.error(setError)._thenRunCallbacks(options, this);
2012         }
2013 
2014         var model = this;
2015 
2016         // If there is any unsaved child, save it first.
2017         model._refreshCache();
2018 
2019 
2020         var unsavedChildren = [];
2021         var unsavedFiles = [];
2022         ML.Object._findUnsavedChildren(model.attributes,
2023           unsavedChildren,
2024           unsavedFiles);
2025         if (unsavedChildren.length + unsavedFiles.length > 0) {
2026           return ML.Object._deepSaveAsync(this.attributes, model).then(function () {
2027             return model.save(null, options);
2028           }, function (error) {
2029             return ML.Promise.error(error)._thenRunCallbacks(options, model);
2030           });
2031         }
2032 
2033         this._startSave();
2034         this._saving = (this._saving || 0) + 1;
2035 
2036         this._allPreviousSaves = this._allPreviousSaves || ML.Promise.as();
2037         this._allPreviousSaves = this._allPreviousSaves._continueWith(function () {
2038           var method = model.id ? 'PUT' : 'POST';
2039 
2040           var json = model._getSaveJSON();
2041 
2042           if (model._fetchWhenSave) {
2043             //Sepcial-case fetchWhenSave when updating object.
2044             json._fetchWhenSave = true;
2045           }
2046 
2047           var route = "classes";
2048           var className = model.className;
2049           if (model.className === "_User" && !model.id) {
2050             // Special-case user sign-up.
2051             route = "users";
2052             className = null;
2053           }
2054           //hook makeRequest in options.
2055           var makeRequest = options._makeRequest || ML._request;
2056           var request = makeRequest(route, className, model.id, method, json);
2057 
2058           request = request.then(function (resp, status, xhr) {
2059             var serverAttrs = model.parse(resp, status, xhr);
2060             if (options.wait) {
2061               serverAttrs = _.extend(attrs || {}, serverAttrs);
2062             }
2063             model._finishSave(serverAttrs);
2064             if (options.wait) {
2065               model.set(current, setOptions);
2066             }
2067             return model;
2068 
2069           }, function (error) {
2070             model._cancelSave();
2071             return ML.Promise.error(error);
2072 
2073           })._thenRunCallbacks(options, model);
2074 
2075           return request;
2076         });
2077         return this._allPreviousSaves;
2078       },
2079 
2080       /**
2081        * Destroy this model on the server if it was already persisted.
2082        * Optimistically removes the model from its collection, if it has one.
2083        * If `wait: true` is passed, waits for the server to respond
2084        * before removal.
2085        *
2086        * @return {ML.Promise} A promise that is fulfilled when the destroy
2087        *     completes.
2088        */
2089       destroy: function (options) {
2090         options = options || {};
2091         var model = this;
2092 
2093         var triggerDestroy = function () {
2094           model.trigger('destroy', model, model.collection, options);
2095         };
2096 
2097         if (!this.id) {
2098           return triggerDestroy();
2099         }
2100 
2101         if (!options.wait) {
2102           triggerDestroy();
2103         }
2104 
2105         var request =
2106           ML._request("classes", this.className, this.id, 'DELETE');
2107         return request.then(function () {
2108           if (options.wait) {
2109             triggerDestroy();
2110           }
2111           return model;
2112         })._thenRunCallbacks(options, this);
2113       },
2114 
2115       /**
2116        * Converts a response into the hash of attributes to be set on the model.
2117        * @ignore
2118        */
2119       parse: function (resp, status, xhr) {
2120         var output = _.clone(resp);
2121         _(["createdAt", "updatedAt"]).each(function (key) {
2122           if (output[key]) {
2123             output[key] = ML._parseDate(output[key]);
2124           }
2125         });
2126         if (!output.updatedAt) {
2127           output.updatedAt = output.createdAt;
2128         }
2129         if (status) {
2130           this._existed = (status !== 201);
2131         }
2132         return output;
2133       },
2134 
2135       /**
2136        * Creates a new model with identical attributes to this one.
2137        * @return {ML.Object}
2138        */
2139       clone: function () {
2140         return new this.constructor(this.attributes);
2141       },
2142 
2143       /**
2144        * Returns true if this object has never been saved to ML.
2145        * @return {Boolean}
2146        */
2147       isNew: function () {
2148         return !this.id;
2149       },
2150 
2151       /**
2152        * Call this method to manually fire a `"change"` event for this model and
2153        * a `"change:attribute"` event for each changed attribute.
2154        * Calling this will cause all objects observing the model to update.
2155        */
2156       change: function (options) {
2157         options = options || {};
2158         var changing = this._changing;
2159         this._changing = true;
2160 
2161         // Silent changes become pending changes.
2162         var self = this;
2163         ML._objectEach(this._silent, function (attr) {
2164           self._pending[attr] = true;
2165         });
2166 
2167         // Silent changes are triggered.
2168         var changes = _.extend({}, options.changes, this._silent);
2169         this._silent = {};
2170         ML._objectEach(changes, function (unused_value, attr) {
2171           self.trigger('change:' + attr, self, self.get(attr), options);
2172         });
2173         if (changing) {
2174           return this;
2175         }
2176 
2177         // This is to get around lint not letting us make a function in a loop.
2178         var deleteChanged = function (value, attr) {
2179           if (!self._pending[attr] && !self._silent[attr]) {
2180             delete self.changed[attr];
2181           }
2182         };
2183 
2184         // Continue firing `"change"` events while there are pending changes.
2185         while (!_.isEmpty(this._pending)) {
2186           this._pending = {};
2187           this.trigger('change', this, options);
2188           // Pending and silent changes still remain.
2189           ML._objectEach(this.changed, deleteChanged);
2190           self._previousAttributes = _.clone(this.attributes);
2191         }
2192 
2193         this._changing = false;
2194         return this;
2195       },
2196 
2197       /**
2198        * Returns true if this object was created by the ML server when the
2199        * object might have already been there (e.g. in the case of a Facebook
2200        * login)
2201        */
2202       existed: function () {
2203         return this._existed;
2204       },
2205 
2206       /**
2207        * Determine if the model has changed since the last <code>"change"</code>
2208        * event.  If you specify an attribute name, determine if that attribute
2209        * has changed.
2210        * @param {String} attr Optional attribute name
2211        * @return {Boolean}
2212        */
2213       hasChanged: function (attr) {
2214         if (!arguments.length) {
2215           return !_.isEmpty(this.changed);
2216         }
2217         return this.changed && _.has(this.changed, attr);
2218       },
2219 
2220       /**
2221        * Returns an object containing all the attributes that have changed, or
2222        * false if there are no changed attributes. Useful for determining what
2223        * parts of a view need to be updated and/or what attributes need to be
2224        * persisted to the server. Unset attributes will be set to undefined.
2225        * You can also pass an attributes object to diff against the model,
2226        * determining if there *would be* a change.
2227        */
2228       changedAttributes: function (diff) {
2229         if (!diff) {
2230           return this.hasChanged() ? _.clone(this.changed) : false;
2231         }
2232         var changed = {};
2233         var old = this._previousAttributes;
2234         ML._objectEach(diff, function (diffVal, attr) {
2235           if (!_.isEqual(old[attr], diffVal)) {
2236             changed[attr] = diffVal;
2237           }
2238         });
2239         return changed;
2240       },
2241 
2242       /**
2243        * Gets the previous value of an attribute, recorded at the time the last
2244        * <code>"change"</code> event was fired.
2245        * @param {String} attr Name of the attribute to get.
2246        */
2247       previous: function (attr) {
2248         if (!arguments.length || !this._previousAttributes) {
2249           return null;
2250         }
2251         return this._previousAttributes[attr];
2252       },
2253 
2254       /**
2255        * Gets all of the attributes of the model at the time of the previous
2256        * <code>"change"</code> event.
2257        * @return {Object}
2258        */
2259       previousAttributes: function () {
2260         return _.clone(this._previousAttributes);
2261       },
2262 
2263       /**
2264        * Checks if the model is currently in a valid state. It's only possible to
2265        * get into an *invalid* state if you're using silent changes.
2266        * @return {Boolean}
2267        */
2268       isValid: function () {
2269         return !this.validate(this.attributes);
2270       },
2271 
2272       /**
2273        * Run validation against a set of incoming attributes, returning `true`
2274        * if all is well. If a specific `error` callback has been passed,
2275        * call that instead of firing the general `"error"` event.
2276        */
2277       _validate: function (attrs, options) {
2278         if (options.silent || !this.validate) {
2279           return true;
2280         }
2281         attrs = _.extend({}, this.attributes, attrs);
2282         var error = this.validate(attrs, options);
2283         if (!error) {
2284           return true;
2285         }
2286         if (options && options.error) {
2287           options.error(this, error, options);
2288         } else {
2289           this.trigger('error', this, error, options);
2290         }
2291         return false;
2292       },
2293 
2294     });

2317   ML.Object.destroyAll = function (objects, options) {
2318     if (objects == null || objects.length == 0) {
2319       return ML.Promise.as()._thenRunCallbacks(options);
2320     }
2321     var dataObject = {
2322       requests: []
2323     };
2324 
2325     objects.forEach(function (obj) {
2326       dataObject.requests.push({
2327         method: 'delete',
2328         path: 'classes/' + objects[0].className + '/' + obj.id
2329       });

2332       ML._request('batch', null, null, 'POST', dataObject);

2336   /**
2337    * Returns the appropriate subclass for making new instances of the given
2338    * className string.
2339    */
2340   ML.Object._getSubclass = function (className) {
2341     if (!_.isString(className)) {
2342       throw "ML.Object._getSubclass requires a string argument.";
2343     }
2344     var ObjectClass = ML.Object._classMap[className];
2345     if (!ObjectClass) {
2346       ObjectClass = ML.Object.extend(className);
2347       ML.Object._classMap[className] = ObjectClass;
2348     }
2349     return ObjectClass;
2350   };

2384   /**
2385    * Creates a new subclass of ML.Object for the given ML class name.
2386    *
2387    * <p>Every extension of a ML class will inherit from the most recent
2388    * previous extension of that class. When a ML.Object is automatically
2389    * created by parsing JSON, it will use the most recent extension of that
2390    * class.</p>
2391    *
2392    * <p>You should call either:<pre>
2393    *     var MyClass = ML.Object.extend("MyClass", {
2394    *         <i>Instance properties</i>
2395    *     }, {
2396    *         <i>Class properties</i>
2397    *     });</pre>
2398    * or, for Backbone compatibility:<pre>
2399    *     var MyClass = ML.Object.extend({
2400    *         className: "MyClass",
2401    *         <i>Other instance properties</i>
2402    *     }, {
2403    *         <i>Class properties</i>
2404    *     });</pre></p>
2405    *
2406    * @param {String} className The name of the ML class backing this model.
2407    * @param {Object} protoProps Instance properties to add to instances of the
2408    *     class returned from this method.
2409    * @param {Object} classProps Class properties to add the class returned from
2410    *     this method.
2411    * @return {Class} A new subclass of ML.Object.
2412    */
2413   ML.Object.extend = function (className, protoProps, classProps) {
2414     // Handle the case with only two args.
2415     if (!_.isString(className)) {
2416       if (className && _.has(className, "className")) {
2417         return ML.Object.extend(className.className, className, protoProps);
2418       } else {
2419         throw new Error(
2420           "ML.Object.extend's first argument should be the className.");
2421       }
2422     }
2423 
2424     // If someone tries to subclass "User", coerce it to the right type.
2425     if (className === "User") {
2426       className = "_User";
2427     }
2428 
2429     var NewClassObject = null;
2430     if (_.has(ML.Object._classMap, className)) {
2431       var OldClassObject = ML.Object._classMap[className];
2432       // This new subclass has been told to extend both from "this" and from
2433       // OldClassObject. This is multiple inheritance, which isn't supported.
2434       // For now, let's just pick one.
2435       NewClassObject = OldClassObject._extend(protoProps, classProps);
2436     } else {
2437       protoProps = protoProps || {};
2438       protoProps.className = className;
2439       NewClassObject = this._extend(protoProps, classProps);
2440     }
2441     // Extending a subclass should reuse the classname automatically.
2442     NewClassObject.extend = function (arg0) {
2443       if (_.isString(arg0) || (arg0 && _.has(arg0, "className"))) {
2444         return ML.Object.extend.apply(NewClassObject, arguments);
2445       }
2446       var newArguments = [className].concat(ML._.toArray(arguments));
2447       return ML.Object.extend.apply(NewClassObject, newArguments);
2448     };
2449     NewClassObject.new = function (attributes, options) {
2450       return new NewClassObject(attributes, options);
2451     };
2452     ML.Object._classMap[className] = NewClassObject;
2453     return NewClassObject;
2454   };

2456   ML.Object._findUnsavedChildren = function (object, children, files) {
2457     ML._traverse(object, function (object) {
2458       if (object instanceof ML.Object) {
2459         object._refreshCache();
2460         if (object.dirty()) {
2461           children.push(object);
2462         }
2463         return;
2464       }
2465 
2466       if (object instanceof ML.File) {
2467         if (!object.url() && !object.id) {
2468           files.push(object);
2469         }
2470         return;
2471       }
2472     });
2473   };
2474 
2475   ML.Object._canBeSerializedAsValue = function (object) {
2476     var canBeSerializedAsValue = true;
2477 
2478     if (object instanceof ML.Object) {
2479       canBeSerializedAsValue = !!object.id;
2480 
2481     } else if (_.isArray(object)) {
2482       ML._arrayEach(object, function (child) {
2483         if (!ML.Object._canBeSerializedAsValue(child)) {
2484           canBeSerializedAsValue = false;
2485         }
2486       });
2487 
2488     } else if (_.isObject(object)) {
2489       ML._objectEach(object, function (child) {
2490         if (!ML.Object._canBeSerializedAsValue(child)) {
2491           canBeSerializedAsValue = false;
2492         }
2493       });
2494     }
2495 
2496     return canBeSerializedAsValue;
2497   };

2499   ML.Object._deepSaveAsync = function (object, model) {
2500     var unsavedChildren = [];
2501     var unsavedFiles = [];
2502     ML.Object._findUnsavedChildren(object, unsavedChildren, unsavedFiles);
2503     if (model) {
2504       unsavedChildren = _.filter(unsavedChildren, function (object) {
2505         return object != model;
2506       });
2507     }
2508 
2509     var promise = ML.Promise.as();
2510     _.each(unsavedFiles, function (file) {
2511       promise = promise.then(function () {
2512         return file.save();
2513       });
2514     });
2515 
2516     var objects = _.uniq(unsavedChildren);
2517     var remaining = _.uniq(objects);
2518 
2519     return promise.then(function () {
2520       return ML.Promise._continueWhile(function () {
2521         return remaining.length > 0;
2522       }, function () {
2523 
2524         // Gather up all the objects that can be saved in this batch.
2525         var batch = [];
2526         var newRemaining = [];
2527         ML._arrayEach(remaining, function (object) {
2528           // Limit batches to 20 objects.
2529           if (batch.length > 20) {
2530             newRemaining.push(object);
2531             return;
2532           }
2533 
2534           if (object._canBeSerialized()) {
2535             batch.push(object);
2536           } else {
2537             newRemaining.push(object);
2538           }
2539         });
2540         remaining = newRemaining;
2541 
2542         // If we can't save any objects, there must be a circular reference.
2543         if (batch.length === 0) {
2544           return ML.Promise.error(
2545             new ML.Error(ML.Error.OTHER_CAUSE,
2546               "Tried to save a batch with a cycle."));
2547         }
2548 
2549         // Reserve a spot in every object's save queue.
2550         var readyToStart = ML.Promise.when(_.map(batch, function (object) {
2551           return object._allPreviousSaves || ML.Promise.as();
2552         }));
2553         var batchFinished = new ML.Promise();
2554         ML._arrayEach(batch, function (object) {
2555           object._allPreviousSaves = batchFinished;
2556         });
2557         // Save a single batch, whether previous saves succeeded or failed.
2558         return readyToStart._continueWith(function () {
2559           return ML._request("batch", null, null, "POST", {
2560             requests: _.map(batch, function (object) {
2561               var json = object._getSaveJSON();
2562               var method = "POST";
2563 
2564               var path = "/2.0/classes/" + object.className;
2565               if (object.id) {
2566                 path = path + "/" + object.id;
2567                 method = "PUT";
2568               }
2569 
2570               object._startSave();
2571 
2572               return {
2573                 method: method,
2574                 path: path,
2575                 body: json
2576               };
2577             })
2578 
2579           }).then(function (response, status, xhr) {
2580             var error;
2581             ML._arrayEach(batch, function (object, i) {
2582               object._finishSave(
2583                 object.parse(response[i], status, xhr));
2584             });
2585             if (error) {
2586               return ML.Promise.error(
2587                 new ML.Error(error.code, error.error));
2588             }
2589 
2590           }).then(function (results) {
2591             batchFinished.resolve(results);
2592             return results;
2593           }, function (error) {
2594             batchFinished.reject(error);
2595             return ML.Promise.error(error);
2596           });
2597         });
2598       });
2599     }).then(function () {
2600       return object;
2601     });
2602   };
2603 
2604 };

2612   /**
2613    * A ML.Op is an atomic operation that can be applied to a field in a
2614    * ML.Object. For example, calling <code>object.set("foo", "bar")</code>
2615    * is an example of a ML.Op.Set. Calling <code>object.unset("foo")</code>
2616    * is a ML.Op.Unset. These operations are stored in a ML.Object and
2617    * sent to the server as part of <code>object.save()</code> operations.
2618    * Instances of ML.Op should be immutable.
2619    *
2620    * You should not create subclasses of ML.Op or instantiate ML.Op
2621    * directly.
2622    */
2623   ML.Op = function() {
2624     this._initialize.apply(this, arguments);
2625   };
2626 
2627   ML.Op.prototype = {
2628     _initialize: function() {}
2629   };
2630 
2631   _.extend(ML.Op, {
2632     /**
2633      * To create a new Op, call ML.Op._extend();
2634      */
2635     _extend: ML._extend,
2636 
2637     // A map of __op string to decoder function.
2638     _opDecoderMap: {},
2639 
2640     /**
2641      * Registers a function to convert a json object with an __op field into an
2642      * instance of a subclass of ML.Op.
2643      */
2644     _registerDecoder: function(opName, decoder) {
2645       ML.Op._opDecoderMap[opName] = decoder;
2646     },
2647 
2648     /**
2649      * Converts a json object into an instance of a subclass of ML.Op.
2650      */
2651     _decode: function(json) {
2652       var decoder = ML.Op._opDecoderMap[json.__op];
2653       if (decoder) {
2654         return decoder(json);
2655       } else {
2656         return undefined;
2657       }
2658     }
2659   });

2666     ML._arrayEach(json.ops, function(nextOp) {
2667       nextOp = ML.Op._decode(nextOp);
2668       op = nextOp._mergeWithPrevious(op);
2669     });
2670     return op;
2671   });

2675    * ML.Object.set, or it is a mutable container that was detected as being
2676    * changed.

2740   /**
2741    * An Increment is an atomic operation where the numeric value for the field
2742    * will be increased by a given amount.
2743    */
2744   ML.Op.Increment = ML.Op._extend(
2745       /** @lends ML.Op.Increment.prototype */ {
2746 
2747     _initialize: function(amount) {
2748       this._amount = amount;
2749     },
2750 
2751     /**
2752      * Returns the amount to increment by.
2753      * @return {Number} the amount to increment by.
2754      */
2755     amount: function() {
2756       return this._amount;
2757     },
2758 
2759     /**
2760      * Returns a JSON version of the operation suitable for sending to ML.
2761      * @return {Object}
2762      */
2763     toJSON: function() {
2764       return { __op: "Increment", amount: this._amount };
2765     },
2766 
2767     _mergeWithPrevious: function(previous) {
2768       if (!previous) {
2769         return this;
2770       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Unset) {
2771         return new ML.Op.Set(this.amount());
2772       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Set) {
2773         return new ML.Op.Set(previous.value() + this.amount());
2774       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Increment) {
2775         return new ML.Op.Increment(this.amount() + previous.amount());
2776       } else {
2777         throw "Op is invalid after previous op.";
2778       }
2779     },
2780 
2781     _estimate: function(oldValue) {
2782       if (!oldValue) {
2783         return this.amount();
2784       }
2785       return oldValue + this.amount();
2786     }
2787   });

2793   /**
2794    * Add is an atomic operation where the given objects will be appended to the
2795    * array that is stored in this field.
2796    */
2797   ML.Op.Add = ML.Op._extend(/** @lends ML.Op.Add.prototype */ {
2798     _initialize: function(objects) {
2799       this._objects = objects;
2800     },

2814     toJSON: function() {
2815       return ML._encode(this.objects());
2816     },
2817 
2818     _mergeWithPrevious: function(previous) {
2819       if (!previous) {
2820         return this;
2821       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Unset) {
2822         return new ML.Op.Set(this.objects());
2823       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Set) {
2824         return new ML.Op.Set(this._estimate(previous.value()));
2825       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Add) {
2826         return new ML.Op.Add(previous.objects().concat(this.objects()));
2827       } else {
2828         throw "Op is invalid after previous op.";
2829       }

2835       } else {
2836         return oldValue.concat(this.objects());
2837       }
2838     }

2866      * Returns a JSON version of the operation suitable for sending to ML.
2867      * @return {Object}
2868      */
2869     toJSON: function() {
2870       return { __op: "AddUnique", objects: ML._encode(this.objects()) };
2871     },
2872 
2873     _mergeWithPrevious: function(previous) {
2874       if (!previous) {
2875         return this;
2876       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Unset) {
2877         return new ML.Op.Set(this.objects());
2878       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Set) {
2879         return new ML.Op.Set(this._estimate(previous.value()));
2880       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.AddUnique) {
2881         return new ML.Op.AddUnique(this._estimate(previous.objects()));
2882       } else {
2883         throw "Op is invalid after previous op.";
2884       }
2885     },
2886 
2887     _estimate: function(oldValue) {
2888       if (!oldValue) {
2889         return _.clone(this.objects());
2890       } else {
2891         // We can't just take the _.uniq(_.union(...)) of oldValue and
2892         // this.objects, because the uniqueness may not apply to oldValue
2893         // (especially if the oldValue was set via .set())
2894         var newValue = _.clone(oldValue);
2895         ML._arrayEach(this.objects(), function(obj) {
2896           if (obj instanceof ML.Object && obj.id) {
2897             var matchingObj = _.find(newValue, function(anObj) {
2898               return (anObj instanceof ML.Object) && (anObj.id === obj.id);
2899             });
2900             if (!matchingObj) {
2901               newValue.push(obj);
2902             } else {
2903               var index = _.indexOf(newValue, matchingObj);
2904               newValue[index] = obj;
2905             }
2906           } else if (!_.contains(newValue, obj)) {
2907             newValue.push(obj);
2908           }
2909         });
2910         return newValue;
2911       }
2912     }
2913   });

2944     _mergeWithPrevious: function(previous) {
2945       if (!previous) {
2946         return this;
2947       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Unset) {
2948         return previous;
2949       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Set) {
2950         return new ML.Op.Set(this._estimate(previous.value()));

2953       } else {

2980   /**
2981    * A Relation operation indicates that the field is an instance of
2982    * ML.Relation, and objects are being added to, or removed from, that

2986       /** @lends ML.Op.Relation.prototype */ {
2987 
2988     _initialize: function(adds, removes) {
2989       this._targetClassName = null;
2990 
2991       var self = this;
2992 
2993       var pointerToId = function(object) {
2994         if (object instanceof ML.Object) {
2995           if (!object.id) {
2996             throw "You can't add an unsaved ML.Object to a relation.";
2997           }
2998           if (!self._targetClassName) {
2999             self._targetClassName = object.className;
3000           }
3001           if (self._targetClassName !== object.className) {
3002             throw "Tried to create a ML.Relation with 2 different types: " +
3003                   self._targetClassName + " and " + object.className + ".";
3004           }
3005           return object.id;
3006         }
3007         return object;
3008       };
3009 
3010       this.relationsToAdd = _.uniq(_.map(adds, pointerToId));
3011       this.relationsToRemove = _.uniq(_.map(removes, pointerToId));
3012     },
3013 
3014     /**
3015      * Returns an array of unfetched ML.Object that are being added to the
3016      * relation.
3017      * @return {Array}
3018      */
3019     added: function() {
3020       var self = this;
3021       return _.map(this.relationsToAdd, function(objectId) {
3022         var object = ML.Object._create(self._targetClassName);
3023         object.id = objectId;
3024         return object;
3025       });
3026     },
3027 
3028     /**
3029      * Returns an array of unfetched ML.Object that are being removed from
3030      * the relation.
3031      * @return {Array}
3032      */
3033     removed: function() {
3034       var self = this;
3035       return _.map(this.relationsToRemove, function(objectId) {
3036         var object = ML.Object._create(self._targetClassName);
3037         object.id = objectId;
3038         return object;
3039       });
3040     },
3041 
3042     /**
3043      * Returns a JSON version of the operation suitable for sending to ML.
3044      * @return {Object}
3045      */
3046     toJSON: function() {
3047       var adds = null;
3048       var removes = null;
3049       var self = this;
3050       var idToPointer = function(id) {
3051         return { __type: 'Pointer',
3052                  className: self._targetClassName,
3053                  objectId: id };
3054       };
3055       var pointers = null;
3056       if (this.relationsToAdd.length > 0) {
3057         pointers = _.map(this.relationsToAdd, idToPointer);
3058         adds = { "__op": "AddRelation", "objects": pointers };
3059       }
3060 
3061       if (this.relationsToRemove.length > 0) {
3062         pointers = _.map(this.relationsToRemove, idToPointer);
3063         removes = { "__op": "RemoveRelation", "objects": pointers };
3064       }
3065 
3066       if (adds && removes) {
3067         return { "__op": "Batch", "ops": [adds, removes]};
3068       }
3069 
3070       return adds || removes || {};
3071     },
3072 
3073     _mergeWithPrevious: function(previous) {
3074       if (!previous) {
3075         return this;
3076       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Unset) {
3077         throw "You can't modify a relation after deleting it.";
3078       } else if (previous instanceof ML.Op.Relation) {
3079         if (previous._targetClassName &&
3080             previous._targetClassName !== this._targetClassName) {
3081           throw "Related object must be of class " + previous._targetClassName +
3082               ", but " + this._targetClassName + " was passed in.";
3083         }
3084         var newAdd = _.union(_.difference(previous.relationsToAdd,
3085                                           this.relationsToRemove),
3086                              this.relationsToAdd);
3087         var newRemove = _.union(_.difference(previous.relationsToRemove,
3088                                              this.relationsToAdd),
3089                                 this.relationsToRemove);
3090 
3091         var newRelation = new ML.Op.Relation(newAdd, newRemove);
3092         newRelation._targetClassName = this._targetClassName;
3093         return newRelation;
3094       } else {
3095         throw "Op is invalid after previous op.";
3096       }
3097     },
3098 
3099     _estimate: function(oldValue, object, key) {
3100       if (!oldValue) {
3101         var relation = new ML.Relation(object, key);
3102         relation.targetClassName = this._targetClassName;
3103       } else if (oldValue instanceof ML.Relation) {
3104         if (this._targetClassName) {
3105           if (oldValue.targetClassName) {
3106             if (oldValue.targetClassName !== this._targetClassName) {
3107               throw "Related object must be a " + oldValue.targetClassName +
3108                   ", but a " + this._targetClassName + " was passed in.";
3109             }
3110           } else {
3111             oldValue.targetClassName = this._targetClassName;
3112           }
3113         }
3114         return oldValue;
3115       } else {
3116         throw "Op is invalid after previous op.";
3117       }
3118     }
3119   });

3122     return new ML.Op.Relation(ML._decode(undefined, json.objects), []);
3123   });
3124   ML.Op._registerDecoder("RemoveRelation", function(json) {
3125     return new ML.Op.Relation([], ML._decode(undefined, json.objects));

3136   /**
3137    * A Promise is returned by async methods as a hook to provide callbacks to be
3138    * called when the async task is fulfilled.
3139    *
3140    * <p>Typical usage would be like:<pre>
3141    *    query.find().then(function(results) {
3142    *      results[0].set("foo", "bar");
3143    *      return results[0].saveAsync();
3144    *    }).then(function(result) {
3145    *      console.log("Updated " + result.id);
3146    *    });
3147    * </pre></p>
3148    * <p>Another example:<pre>
3149    *    var promise = new ML.Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
3150    *      resolve(42);
3151    *    });
3152    *    promise.then(function(value){
3153    *      console.log(value);
3154    *    }).catch(function(error){
3155    *      console.error(error);
3156    *    });
3157    * </pre></p>
3158    * @param {Function} fn An optional function with two arguments resolve
3159    *                   and reject.The first argument fulfills the promise,
3160    *                   the second argument rejects it. We can call these
3161     *                  functions, once our operation is completed.
3162    * @see ML.Promise.prototype.then
3163    * @class
3164    */
3165     this._resolved = false;
3166     this._rejected = false;
3167     this._resolvedCallbacks = [];
3168     this._rejectedCallbacks = [];
3169 
3170     this.doResolve(fn);
