7942   // Determines whether to execute a function as a constructor
7943   // or a normal function with the provided arguments
7944   var executeBound = function(sourceFunc, boundFunc, context, callingContext, args) {
7945     if (!(callingContext instanceof boundFunc)) return sourceFunc.apply(context, args);
7946     var self = baseCreate(sourceFunc.prototype);
7947     var result = sourceFunc.apply(self, args);
7948     if (_.isObject(result)) return result;
7949     return self;
7950   };
7951 
7952   // Create a function bound to a given object (assigning `this`, and arguments,
7953   // optionally). Delegates to **ECMAScript 5**'s native `Function.bind` if
7954   // available.
7955   _.bind = function(func, context) {
7956     if (nativeBind && func.bind === nativeBind) return nativeBind.apply(func, slice.call(arguments, 1));
7957     if (!_.isFunction(func)) throw new TypeError('Bind must be called on a function');
7958     var args = slice.call(arguments, 2);
7959     var bound = function() {
7960       return executeBound(func, bound, context, this, args.concat(slice.call(arguments)));
7961     };
7962     return bound;
7963   };
7964 
7965   // Partially apply a function by creating a version that has had some of its
7966   // arguments pre-filled, without changing its dynamic `this` context. _ acts
7967   // as a placeholder, allowing any combination of arguments to be pre-filled.
7968   _.partial = function(func) {
7969     var boundArgs = slice.call(arguments, 1);
7970     var bound = function() {
7971       var position = 0, length = boundArgs.length;
7972       var args = Array(length);
7973       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
7974         args[i] = boundArgs[i] === _ ? arguments[position++] : boundArgs[i];
7975       }
7976       while (position < arguments.length) args.push(arguments[position++]);
7977       return executeBound(func, bound, this, this, args);
7978     };
7979     return bound;
7980   };
7981 
7982   // Bind a number of an object's methods to that object. Remaining arguments
7983   // are the method names to be bound. Useful for ensuring that all callbacks
7984   // defined on an object belong to it.
7985   _.bindAll = function(obj) {
7986     var i, length = arguments.length, key;
7987     if (length <= 1) throw new Error('bindAll must be passed function names');
7988     for (i = 1; i < length; i++) {
7989       key = arguments[i];
7990       obj[key] = _.bind(obj[key], obj);
7991     }
7992     return obj;
7993   };

7995   // Memoize an expensive function by storing its results.
7996   _.memoize = function(func, hasher) {
7997     var memoize = function(key) {
7998       var cache = memoize.cache;
7999       var address = '' + (hasher ? hasher.apply(this, arguments) : key);
8000       if (!_.has(cache, address)) cache[address] = func.apply(this, arguments);
8001       return cache[address];
8002     };
8003     memoize.cache = {};
8004     return memoize;
8005   };

8007   // Delays a function for the given number of milliseconds, and then calls
8008   // it with the arguments supplied.
8009   _.delay = function(func, wait) {
8010     var args = slice.call(arguments, 2);
8011     return setTimeout(function(){
8012       return func.apply(null, args);
8013     }, wait);
8014   };

8016   // Defers a function, scheduling it to run after the current call stack has
8017   // cleared.
8018   _.defer = _.partial(_.delay, _, 1);
8019 
8020   // Returns a function, that, when invoked, will only be triggered at most once
8021   // during a given window of time. Normally, the throttled function will run
8022   // as much as it can, without ever going more than once per `wait` duration;
8023   // but if you'd like to disable the execution on the leading edge, pass
8024   // `{leading: false}`. To disable execution on the trailing edge, ditto.
8025   _.throttle = function(func, wait, options) {
8026     var context, args, result;
8027     var timeout = null;
8028     var previous = 0;
8029     if (!options) options = {};
8030     var later = function() {
8031       previous = options.leading === false ? 0 : _.now();
8032       timeout = null;
8033       result = func.apply(context, args);
8034       if (!timeout) context = args = null;
8035     };
8036     return function() {
8037       var now = _.now();
8038       if (!previous && options.leading === false) previous = now;
8039       var remaining = wait - (now - previous);
8040       context = this;
8041       args = arguments;
8042       if (remaining <= 0 || remaining > wait) {
8043         if (timeout) {
8044           clearTimeout(timeout);
8045           timeout = null;
8046         }
8047         previous = now;
8048         result = func.apply(context, args);
8049         if (!timeout) context = args = null;
8050       } else if (!timeout && options.trailing !== false) {
8051         timeout = setTimeout(later, remaining);
8052       }
8053       return result;
8054     };
8055   };
8056 
8057   // Returns a function, that, as long as it continues to be invoked, will not
8058   // be triggered. The function will be called after it stops being called for
8059   // N milliseconds. If `immediate` is passed, trigger the function on the
8060   // leading edge, instead of the trailing.
8061   _.debounce = function(func, wait, immediate) {
8062     var timeout, args, context, timestamp, result;
8063 
8064     var later = function() {
8065       var last = _.now() - timestamp;
8066 
8067       if (last < wait && last >= 0) {
8068         timeout = setTimeout(later, wait - last);
8069       } else {
8070         timeout = null;
8071         if (!immediate) {
8072           result = func.apply(context, args);
8073           if (!timeout) context = args = null;
8074         }
8075       }
8076     };
8077 
8078     return function() {
8079       context = this;
8080       args = arguments;
8081       timestamp = _.now();
8082       var callNow = immediate && !timeout;
8083       if (!timeout) timeout = setTimeout(later, wait);
8084       if (callNow) {
8085         result = func.apply(context, args);
8086         context = args = null;
8087       }
8088 
8089       return result;
8090     };
8091   };
8092 
8093   // Returns the first function passed as an argument to the second,
8094   // allowing you to adjust arguments, run code before and after, and
8095   // conditionally execute the original function.
8096   _.wrap = function(func, wrapper) {
8097     return _.partial(wrapper, func);
8098   };

8100   // Returns a negated version of the passed-in predicate.
8101   _.negate = function(predicate) {
8102     return function() {
8103       return !predicate.apply(this, arguments);
8104     };
8105   };
8106 
8107   // Returns a function that is the composition of a list of functions, each
8108   // consuming the return value of the function that follows.
8109   _.compose = function() {
8110     var args = arguments;
8111     var start = args.length - 1;
8112     return function() {
8113       var i = start;
8114       var result = args[start].apply(this, arguments);
8115       while (i--) result = args[i].call(this, result);
8116       return result;
8117     };
8118   };
8119 
8120   // Returns a function that will only be executed on and after the Nth call.
8121   _.after = function(times, func) {
8122     return function() {
8123       if (--times < 1) {
8124         return func.apply(this, arguments);
8125       }
8126     };
8127   };
8128 
8129   // Returns a function that will only be executed up to (but not including) the Nth call.
8130   _.before = function(times, func) {
8131     var memo;
8132     return function() {
8133       if (--times > 0) {
8134         memo = func.apply(this, arguments);
8135       }
8136       if (times <= 1) func = null;
8137       return memo;
8138     };
8139   };
8140 
8141   // Returns a function that will be executed at most one time, no matter how
8142   // often you call it. Useful for lazy initialization.
8143   _.once = _.partial(_.before, 2);

8148   // Keys in IE < 9 that won't be iterated by `for key in ...` and thus missed.
8149   var hasEnumBug = !{toString: null}.propertyIsEnumerable('toString');
8150   var nonEnumerableProps = ['valueOf', 'isPrototypeOf', 'toString',
8151                       'propertyIsEnumerable', 'hasOwnProperty', 'toLocaleString'];
8152 
8153   function collectNonEnumProps(obj, keys) {
8154     var nonEnumIdx = nonEnumerableProps.length;
8155     var constructor = obj.constructor;
8156     var proto = (_.isFunction(constructor) && constructor.prototype) || ObjProto;
8157 
8158     // Constructor is a special case.
8159     var prop = 'constructor';
8160     if (_.has(obj, prop) && !_.contains(keys, prop)) keys.push(prop);
8161 
8162     while (nonEnumIdx--) {
8163       prop = nonEnumerableProps[nonEnumIdx];
8164       if (prop in obj && obj[prop] !== proto[prop] && !_.contains(keys, prop)) {
8165         keys.push(prop);
8166       }
8167     }
8168   }
8169 
8170   // Retrieve the names of an object's own properties.
8171   // Delegates to **ECMAScript 5**'s native `Object.keys`
8172   _.keys = function(obj) {
8173     if (!_.isObject(obj)) return [];
8174     if (nativeKeys) return nativeKeys(obj);
8175     var keys = [];
8176     for (var key in obj) if (_.has(obj, key)) keys.push(key);
8177     // Ahem, IE < 9.
8178     if (hasEnumBug) collectNonEnumProps(obj, keys);
8179     return keys;
8180   };
8181 
8182   // Retrieve all the property names of an object.
8183   _.allKeys = function(obj) {
8184     if (!_.isObject(obj)) return [];
8185     var keys = [];
8186     for (var key in obj) keys.push(key);
8187     // Ahem, IE < 9.
8188     if (hasEnumBug) collectNonEnumProps(obj, keys);
8189     return keys;
8190   };
8191 
8192   // Retrieve the values of an object's properties.
8193   _.values = function(obj) {
8194     var keys = _.keys(obj);
8195     var length = keys.length;
8196     var values = Array(length);
8197     for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8198       values[i] = obj[keys[i]];
8199     }
8200     return values;
8201   };

8203   // Returns the results of applying the iteratee to each element of the object
8204   // In contrast to _.map it returns an object
8205   _.mapObject = function(obj, iteratee, context) {
8206     iteratee = cb(iteratee, context);
8207     var keys =  _.keys(obj),
8208           length = keys.length,
8209           results = {},
8210           currentKey;
8211       for (var index = 0; index < length; index++) {
8212         currentKey = keys[index];
8213         results[currentKey] = iteratee(obj[currentKey], currentKey, obj);
8214       }
8215       return results;
8216   };

8218   // Convert an object into a list of `[key, value]` pairs.
8219   _.pairs = function(obj) {
8220     var keys = _.keys(obj);
8221     var length = keys.length;
8222     var pairs = Array(length);
8223     for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8224       pairs[i] = [keys[i], obj[keys[i]]];
8225     }
8226     return pairs;
8227   };

8229   // Invert the keys and values of an object. The values must be serializable.
8230   _.invert = function(obj) {
8231     var result = {};
8232     var keys = _.keys(obj);
8233     for (var i = 0, length = keys.length; i < length; i++) {
8234       result[obj[keys[i]]] = keys[i];
8235     }
8236     return result;
8237   };

8239   // Return a sorted list of the function names available on the object.
8240   // Aliased as `methods`
8241   _.functions = _.methods = function(obj) {
8242     var names = [];
8243     for (var key in obj) {
8244       if (_.isFunction(obj[key])) names.push(key);
8245     }
8246     return names.sort();

8249   // Extend a given object with all the properties in passed-in object(s).

8252   // Assigns a given object with all the own properties in the passed-in object(s)
8253   // (https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/assign)
8254   _.extendOwn = _.assign = createAssigner(_.keys);

8256   // Returns the first key on an object that passes a predicate test
8257   _.findKey = function(obj, predicate, context) {
8258     predicate = cb(predicate, context);
8259     var keys = _.keys(obj), key;
8260     for (var i = 0, length = keys.length; i < length; i++) {
8261       key = keys[i];
8262       if (predicate(obj[key], key, obj)) return key;
8263     }
8264   };

8266   // Return a copy of the object only containing the whitelisted properties.
8267   _.pick = function(object, oiteratee, context) {
8268     var result = {}, obj = object, iteratee, keys;
8269     if (obj == null) return result;
8270     if (_.isFunction(oiteratee)) {
8271       keys = _.allKeys(obj);
8272       iteratee = optimizeCb(oiteratee, context);
8273     } else {
8274       keys = flatten(arguments, false, false, 1);
8275       iteratee = function(value, key, obj) { return key in obj; };
8276       obj = Object(obj);
8277     }
8278     for (var i = 0, length = keys.length; i < length; i++) {
8279       var key = keys[i];
8280       var value = obj[key];
8281       if (iteratee(value, key, obj)) result[key] = value;
8282     }
8283     return result;
8284   };
8285 
8286    // Return a copy of the object without the blacklisted properties.
8287   _.omit = function(obj, iteratee, context) {
8288     if (_.isFunction(iteratee)) {
8289       iteratee = _.negate(iteratee);
8290     } else {
8291       var keys = _.map(flatten(arguments, false, false, 1), String);
8292       iteratee = function(value, key) {
8293         return !_.contains(keys, key);
8294       };
8295     }
8296     return _.pick(obj, iteratee, context);
8297   };

8311   // Create a (shallow-cloned) duplicate of an object.

8314     return _.isArray(obj) ? obj.slice() : _.extend({}, obj);

8317   // Invokes interceptor with the obj, and then returns obj.
8318   // The primary purpose of this method is to "tap into" a method chain, in
8319   // order to perform operations on intermediate results within the chain.
8320   _.tap = function(obj, interceptor) {
8321     interceptor(obj);

8325   // Returns whether an object has a given set of `key:value` pairs.
8326   _.isMatch = function(object, attrs) {
8327     var keys = _.keys(attrs), length = keys.length;
8328     if (object == null) return !length;
8329     var obj = Object(object);
8330     for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8331       var key = keys[i];
8332       if (attrs[key] !== obj[key] || !(key in obj)) return false;
8333     }
8334     return true;
8335   };
8336 
8337 
8338   // Internal recursive comparison function for `isEqual`.
8339   var eq = function(a, b, aStack, bStack) {
8340     // Identical objects are equal. `0 === -0`, but they aren't identical.
8341     // See the [Harmony `egal` proposal](http://wiki.ecmascript.org/doku.php?id=harmony:egal).
8342     if (a === b) return a !== 0 || 1 / a === 1 / b;
8343     // A strict comparison is necessary because `null == undefined`.
8344     if (a == null || b == null) return a === b;
8345     // Unwrap any wrapped objects.
8346     if (a instanceof _) a = a._wrapped;
8347     if (b instanceof _) b = b._wrapped;
8348     // Compare `[[Class]]` names.
8349     var className = toString.call(a);
8350     if (className !== toString.call(b)) return false;
8351     switch (className) {
8352       // Strings, numbers, regular expressions, dates, and booleans are compared by value.
8353       case '[object RegExp]':
8354       // RegExps are coerced to strings for comparison (Note: '' + /a/i === '/a/i')
8355       case '[object String]':
8356         // Primitives and their corresponding object wrappers are equivalent; thus, `"5"` is
8357         // equivalent to `new String("5")`.
8358         return '' + a === '' + b;
8359       case '[object Number]':
8360         // `NaN`s are equivalent, but non-reflexive.
8361         // Object(NaN) is equivalent to NaN
8362         if (+a !== +a) return +b !== +b;
8363         // An `egal` comparison is performed for other numeric values.
8364         return +a === 0 ? 1 / +a === 1 / b : +a === +b;
8365       case '[object Date]':
8366       case '[object Boolean]':
8367         // Coerce dates and booleans to numeric primitive values. Dates are compared by their
8368         // millisecond representations. Note that invalid dates with millisecond representations
8369         // of `NaN` are not equivalent.
8370         return +a === +b;
8371     }
8372 
8373     var areArrays = className === '[object Array]';
8374     if (!areArrays) {
8375       if (typeof a != 'object' || typeof b != 'object') return false;
8376 
8377       // Objects with different constructors are not equivalent, but `Object`s or `Array`s
8378       // from different frames are.
8379       var aCtor = a.constructor, bCtor = b.constructor;
8380       if (aCtor !== bCtor && !(_.isFunction(aCtor) && aCtor instanceof aCtor &&
8381                                _.isFunction(bCtor) && bCtor instanceof bCtor)
8382                           && ('constructor' in a && 'constructor' in b)) {
8383         return false;
8384       }
8385     }
8386     // Assume equality for cyclic structures. The algorithm for detecting cyclic
8387     // structures is adapted from ES 5.1 section 15.12.3, abstract operation `JO`.
8388 
8389     // Initializing stack of traversed objects.
8390     // It's done here since we only need them for objects and arrays comparison.
8391     aStack = aStack || [];
8392     bStack = bStack || [];
8393     var length = aStack.length;
8394     while (length--) {
8395       // Linear search. Performance is inversely proportional to the number of
8396       // unique nested structures.
8397       if (aStack[length] === a) return bStack[length] === b;
8398     }
8399 
8400     // Add the first object to the stack of traversed objects.
8401     aStack.push(a);
8402     bStack.push(b);
8403 
8404     // Recursively compare objects and arrays.
8405     if (areArrays) {
8406       // Compare array lengths to determine if a deep comparison is necessary.
8407       length = a.length;
8408       if (length !== b.length) return false;
8409       // Deep compare the contents, ignoring non-numeric properties.
8410       while (length--) {
8411         if (!eq(a[length], b[length], aStack, bStack)) return false;
8412       }
8413     } else {
8414       // Deep compare objects.
8415       var keys = _.keys(a), key;
8416       length = keys.length;
8417       // Ensure that both objects contain the same number of properties before comparing deep equality.
8418       if (_.keys(b).length !== length) return false;
8419       while (length--) {
8420         // Deep compare each member
8421         key = keys[length];
8422         if (!(_.has(b, key) && eq(a[key], b[key], aStack, bStack))) return false;
8423       }
8424     }
8425     // Remove the first object from the stack of traversed objects.
8426     aStack.pop();
8427     bStack.pop();
8428     return true;
8429   };
8430 
8431   // Perform a deep comparison to check if two objects are equal.
8432   _.isEqual = function(a, b) {
8433     return eq(a, b);
8434   };
8435 
8436   // Is a given array, string, or object empty?
8437   // An "empty" object has no enumerable own-properties.
8438   _.isEmpty = function(obj) {
8439     if (obj == null) return true;
8440     if (isArrayLike(obj) && (_.isArray(obj) || _.isString(obj) || _.isArguments(obj))) return obj.length === 0;
8441     return _.keys(obj).length === 0;
8442   };

8557   // Run a function **n** times.
8558   _.times = function(n, iteratee, context) {
8559     var accum = Array(Math.max(0, n));
8560     iteratee = optimizeCb(iteratee, context, 1);
8561     for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) accum[i] = iteratee(i);
8562     return accum;

8565   // Return a random integer between min and max (inclusive).
8566   _.random = function(min, max) {
8567     if (max == null) {
8568       max = min;
8569       min = 0;
8570     }
8571     return min + Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min + 1));
8572   };

8579    // List of HTML entities for escaping.
8580   var escapeMap = {
8581     '&': '&',
8582     '<': '<',
8583     '>': '>',
8584     '"': '"',
8585     "'": ''',
8586     '`': '`'
8587   };
8588   var unescapeMap = _.invert(escapeMap);
8589 
8590   // Functions for escaping and unescaping strings to/from HTML interpolation.
8591   var createEscaper = function(map) {
8592     var escaper = function(match) {
8593       return map[match];
8594     };
8595     // Regexes for identifying a key that needs to be escaped
8596     var source = '(?:' + _.keys(map).join('|') + ')';
8597     var testRegexp = RegExp(source);
8598     var replaceRegexp = RegExp(source, 'g');
8599     return function(string) {
8600       string = string == null ? '' : '' + string;
8601       return testRegexp.test(string) ? string.replace(replaceRegexp, escaper) : string;
8602     };
8603   };
8604   _.escape = createEscaper(escapeMap);
8605   _.unescape = createEscaper(unescapeMap);
8606 
8607   // If the value of the named `property` is a function then invoke it with the
8608   // `object` as context; otherwise, return it.
8609   _.result = function(object, property, fallback) {
8610     var value = object == null ? void 0 : object[property];
8611     if (value === void 0) {
8612       value = fallback;
8613     }
8614     return _.isFunction(value) ? value.call(object) : value;
8615   };

8617   // Generate a unique integer id (unique within the entire client session).
8618   // Useful for temporary DOM ids.
8619   var idCounter = 0;
8620   _.uniqueId = function(prefix) {
8621     var id = ++idCounter + '';
8622     return prefix ? prefix + id : id;
8623   };
8624 
8625   // By default, Underscore uses ERB-style template delimiters, change the
8626   // following template settings to use alternative delimiters.
8627   _.templateSettings = {
8628     evaluate    : /<%([\s\S]+?)%>/g,
8629     interpolate : /<%=([\s\S]+?)%>/g,
8630     escape      : /<%-([\s\S]+?)%>/g
8631   };
8632 
8633   // When customizing `templateSettings`, if you don't want to define an
8634   // interpolation, evaluation or escaping regex, we need one that is
8635   // guaranteed not to match.
8636   var noMatch = /(.)^/;
8637 
8638   // Certain characters need to be escaped so that they can be put into a
8639   // string literal.
8640   var escapes = {
8641     "'":      "'",
8642     '\\':     '\\',
8643     '\r':     'r',
8644     '\n':     'n',
8645     '\u2028': 'u2028',
8646     '\u2029': 'u2029'
8647   };
8648 
8649   var escaper = /\\|'|\r|\n|\u2028|\u2029/g;
8650 
8651   var escapeChar = function(match) {
8652     return '\\' + escapes[match];
8653   };
8654 
8655   // JavaScript micro-templating, similar to John Resig's implementation.
8656   // Underscore templating handles arbitrary delimiters, preserves whitespace,
8657   // and correctly escapes quotes within interpolated code.
8658   // NB: `oldSettings` only exists for backwards compatibility.
8659   _.template = function(text, settings, oldSettings) {
8660     if (!settings && oldSettings) settings = oldSettings;
8661     settings = _.defaults({}, settings, _.templateSettings);
8662 
8663     // Combine delimiters into one regular expression via alternation.
8664     var matcher = RegExp([
8665       (settings.escape || noMatch).source,
8666       (settings.interpolate || noMatch).source,
8667       (settings.evaluate || noMatch).source
8668     ].join('|') + '|$', 'g');
8669 
8670     // Compile the template source, escaping string literals appropriately.
8671     var index = 0;
8672     var source = "__p+='";
8673     text.replace(matcher, function(match, escape, interpolate, evaluate, offset) {
8674       source += text.slice(index, offset).replace(escaper, escapeChar);
8675       index = offset + match.length;
8676 
8677       if (escape) {
8678         source += "'+\n((__t=(" + escape + "))==null?'':_.escape(__t))+\n'";
8679       } else if (interpolate) {
8680         source += "'+\n((__t=(" + interpolate + "))==null?'':__t)+\n'";
8681       } else if (evaluate) {
8682         source += "';\n" + evaluate + "\n__p+='";
8683       }
8684 
8685       // Adobe VMs need the match returned to produce the correct offest.
8686       return match;
8687     });
8688     source += "';\n";
8689 
8690     // If a variable is not specified, place data values in local scope.
8691     if (!settings.variable) source = 'with(obj||{}){\n' + source + '}\n';
8692 
8693     source = "var __t,__p='',__j=Array.prototype.join," +
8694       "print=function(){__p+=__j.call(arguments,'');};\n" +
8695       source + 'return __p;\n';
8696 
8697     try {
8698       var render = new Function(settings.variable || 'obj', '_', source);
8699     } catch (e) {
8700       e.source = source;
8701       throw e;
8702     }
8703 
8704     var template = function(data) {
8705       return render.call(this, data, _);
8706     };
8707 
8708     // Provide the compiled source as a convenience for precompilation.
8709     var argument = settings.variable || 'obj';
8710     template.source = 'function(' + argument + '){\n' + source + '}';
8711 
8712     return template;
8713   };
8714 
8715   // Add a "chain" function. Start chaining a wrapped Underscore object.
8716   _.chain = function(obj) {
8717     var instance = _(obj);
8718     instance._chain = true;
8719     return instance;
8720   };

8722   // OOP
8723   // ---------------
8724   // If Underscore is called as a function, it returns a wrapped object that
8725   // can be used OO-style. This wrapper holds altered versions of all the
8726   // underscore functions. Wrapped objects may be chained.
8727 
8728   // Helper function to continue chaining intermediate results.

8807 function typeOf(type) {
8808   return function (object) {
8809     return Object.prototype.toString.call(object) === "[object " + type + "]";
8810   };
8811 }

8817 function each(object, factory) {
8818   for (var i = 0, l = object.length; i < l; i++) {
8819     if (factory.call(object, object[i], i) === false) {
8820       break;
8821     }
8822   }

8825 // UserAgent Detector.
8826 // @param {String} ua, userAgent.
8827 // @param {Object} expression
8828 // @return {Object}
8829 //    返回 null 表示当前表达式未匹配成功。
8830 function detect(name, expression, ua) {
8831   var expr = isFunction(expression) ? expression.call(null, ua) : expression;
8832   if (!expr) {
8833     return null;
8834   }
8835   var info = {
8836     name: name,
8837     version: NA_VERSION,
8838     codename: ""
8839   };
8840   if (expr === true) {
8841     return info;
8842   } else if (isString(expr)) {
8843     if (ua.indexOf(expr) !== -1) {
8844       return info;
8845     }
8846   } else if (isObject(expr)) {
8847     if (expr.hasOwnProperty("version")) {
8848       info.version = expr.version;
8849     }
8850     return info;
8851   } else if (isRegExp(expr)) {
8852     var m = expr.exec(ua);
8853     if (m) {
8854       if (m.length >= 2 && m[1]) {
8855         info.version = m[1].replace(/_/g, ".");
8856       } else {
8857         info.version = NA_VERSION;
8858       }
8859       return info;
8860     }
8861   }
8862 }

8869     if (d) {
8870       detected = d;
8871       return false;
8872     }
8873   });
8874   factory.call(detector, detected.name, detected.version);
8875 }

9813 // The IsCallable() check in the Array functions
9814 // has been replaced with a strict check on the
9815 // internal class of the object to trap cases where
9816 // the provided function was actually a regular
9817 // expression literal, which in V8 and
9818 // JavaScriptCore is a typeof "function".  Only in
9819 // V8 are regular expression literals permitted as
9820 // reduce parameters, so it is desirable in the
9821 // general case for the shim to match the more
9822 // strict and common behavior of rejecting regular
9823 // expressions.
9824 
9825 // ES5 15.4.4.18
9826 // http://es5.github.com/#x15.4.4.18
9827 // https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/array/forEach
9828 
9829 // Check failure of by-index access of string characters (IE < 9)
9830 // and failure of `0 in boxedString` (Rhino)
9831 var boxedString = $Object('a');
9832 var splitString = boxedString[0] !== 'a' || !(0 in boxedString);

9834 var properlyBoxesContext = function properlyBoxed(method) {
9835     // Check node 0.6.21 bug where third parameter is not boxed
9836     var properlyBoxesNonStrict = true;
9837     var properlyBoxesStrict = true;
9838     var threwException = false;
9839     if (method) {
9840         try {
9841             method.call('foo', function (_, __, context) {
9842                 if (typeof context !== 'object') {
9843                     properlyBoxesNonStrict = false;
9844                 }
9845             });
9846 
9847             method.call([1], function () {
9848                 'use strict';
9849 
9850                 properlyBoxesStrict = typeof this === 'string';
9851             }, 'x');
9852         } catch (e) {
9853             threwException = true;
9854         }
9855     }
9856     return !!method && !threwException && properlyBoxesNonStrict && properlyBoxesStrict;
9857 };

9859 defineProperties(ArrayPrototype, {
9860     forEach: function forEach(callbackfn/*, thisArg*/) {
9861         var object = ES.ToObject(this);
9862         var self = splitString && isString(this) ? strSplit(this, '') : object;
9863         var i = -1;
9864         var length = ES.ToUint32(self.length);
9865         var T;
9866         if (arguments.length > 1) {
9867           T = arguments[1];
9868         }
9869 
9870         // If no callback function or if callback is not a callable function
9871         if (!isCallable(callbackfn)) {
9872             throw new TypeError('Array.prototype.forEach callback must be a function');
9873         }
9874 
9875         while (++i < length) {
9876             if (i in self) {
9877                 // Invoke the callback function with call, passing arguments:
9878                 // context, property value, property key, thisArg object
9879                 if (typeof T === 'undefined') {
9880                     callbackfn(self[i], i, object);
9881                 } else {
9882                     callbackfn.call(T, self[i], i, object);
9883                 }
9884             }
9885         }
9886     }
9887 }, !properlyBoxesContext(ArrayPrototype.forEach));

10016 defineProperties(ArrayPrototype, {
10017     reduce: function reduce(callbackfn/*, initialValue*/) {
10018         var object = ES.ToObject(this);
10019         var self = splitString && isString(this) ? strSplit(this, '') : object;
10020         var length = ES.ToUint32(self.length);
10021 
10022         // If no callback function or if callback is not a callable function
10023         if (!isCallable(callbackfn)) {
10024             throw new TypeError('Array.prototype.reduce callback must be a function');
10025         }
10026 
10027         // no value to return if no initial value and an empty array
10028         if (length === 0 && arguments.length === 1) {
10029             throw new TypeError('reduce of empty array with no initial value');
10030         }
10031 
10032         var i = 0;
10033         var result;
10034         if (arguments.length >= 2) {
10035             result = arguments[1];
10036         } else {
10037             do {
10038                 if (i in self) {
10039                     result = self[i++];
10040                     break;
10041                 }
10042 
10043                 // if array contains no values, no initial value to return
10044                 if (++i >= length) {
10045                     throw new TypeError('reduce of empty array with no initial value');
10046                 }
10047             } while (true);
10048         }
10049 
10050         for (; i < length; i++) {
10051             if (i in self) {
10052                 result = callbackfn(result, self[i], i, object);

10232 defineProperties(ArrayPrototype, {
10233     splice: function splice(start, deleteCount) {
10234         var O = ES.ToObject(this);
10235         var A = [];
10236         var len = ES.ToUint32(O.length);
10237         var relativeStart = ES.ToInteger(start);
10238         var actualStart = relativeStart < 0 ? max((len + relativeStart), 0) : min(relativeStart, len);
10239         var actualDeleteCount = min(max(ES.ToInteger(deleteCount), 0), len - actualStart);
10240 
10241         var k = 0;
10242         var from;
10243         while (k < actualDeleteCount) {
10244             from = $String(actualStart + k);
10245             if (owns(O, from)) {
10246                 A[k] = O[from];
10247             }
10248             k += 1;
10249         }
10250 
10251         var items = arraySlice(arguments, 2);
10252         var itemCount = items.length;
10253         var to;
10254         if (itemCount < actualDeleteCount) {
10255             k = actualStart;
10256             var maxK = len - actualDeleteCount;
10257             while (k < maxK) {
10258                 from = $String(k + actualDeleteCount);
10259                 to = $String(k + itemCount);
10260                 if (owns(O, from)) {
10261                     O[to] = O[from];
10262                 } else {
10263                     delete O[to];
10264                 }
10265                 k += 1;
10266             }
10267             k = len;
10268             var minK = len - actualDeleteCount + itemCount;
10269             while (k > minK) {
10270                 delete O[k - 1];
10271                 k -= 1;
10272             }
10273         } else if (itemCount > actualDeleteCount) {
10274             k = len - actualDeleteCount;
10275             while (k > actualStart) {
10276                 from = $String(k + actualDeleteCount - 1);
10277                 to = $String(k + itemCount - 1);
10278                 if (owns(O, from)) {
10279                     O[to] = O[from];
10280                 } else {
10281                     delete O[to];
10282                 }
10283                 k -= 1;
10284             }
10285         }
10286         k = actualStart;
10287         for (var i = 0; i < items.length; ++i) {
10288             O[k] = items[i];
10289             k += 1;
10290         }
10291         O.length = len - actualDeleteCount + itemCount;
10292 
10293         return A;
10294     }
10295 }, !spliceWorksWithLargeSparseArrays || !spliceWorksWithSmallSparseArrays);

10511                     pushCall(theKeys, dontEnum);
10512                 }
10513             }
10514         }

10516     }

10741 defineProperties(Date.prototype, {
10742     toISOString: function toISOString() {
10743         if (!isFinite(this) || !isFinite(getTime(this))) {
10744             // Adope Photoshop requires the second check.
10745             throw new RangeError('Date.prototype.toISOString called on non-finite value.');
10746         }

10748         var year = originalGetUTCFullYear(this);
10749 
10750         var month = originalGetUTCMonth(this);
10751         // see https://github.com/es-shims/es5-shim/issues/111
10752         year += Math.floor(month / 12);
10753         month = (month % 12 + 12) % 12;
10754 
10755         // the date time string format is specified in 15.9.1.15.
10756         var result = [month + 1, originalGetUTCDate(this), originalGetUTCHours(this), originalGetUTCMinutes(this), originalGetUTCSeconds(this)];
10757         year = (
10758             (year < 0 ? '-' : (year > 9999 ? '+' : '')) +
10759             strSlice('00000' + Math.abs(year), (0 <= year && year <= 9999) ? -4 : -6)
10760         );
10761 
10762         for (var i = 0; i < result.length; ++i) {
10763           // pad months, days, hours, minutes, and seconds to have two digits.
10764           result[i] = strSlice('00' + result[i], -2);
10765         }
10766         // pad milliseconds to have three digits.
10767         return (
10768             year + '-' + arraySlice(result, 0, 2).join('-') +
10769             'T' + arraySlice(result, 2).join(':') + '.' +
10770             strSlice('000' + originalGetUTCMilliseconds(this), -3) + 'Z'
10771         );
10772     }

10791 if (!dateToJSONIsSupported) {
10792     Date.prototype.toJSON = function toJSON(key) {
10793         // When the toJSON method is called with argument key, the following
10794         // steps are taken:
10795 
10796         // 1.  Let O be the result of calling ToObject, giving it the this
10797         // value as its argument.
10798         // 2. Let tv be ES.ToPrimitive(O, hint Number).
10799         var O = $Object(this);
10800         var tv = ES.ToPrimitive(O);
10801         // 3. If tv is a Number and is not finite, return null.
10802         if (typeof tv === 'number' && !isFinite(tv)) {
10803             return null;
10804         }
10805         // 4. Let toISO be the result of calling the [[Get]] internal method of
10806         // O with argument "toISOString".
10807         var toISO = O.toISOString;
10808         // 5. If IsCallable(toISO) is false, throw a TypeError exception.
10809         if (!isCallable(toISO)) {
10810             throw new TypeError('toISOString property is not callable');
10811         }
10812         // 6. Return the result of calling the [[Call]] internal method of
10813         //  toISO with O as the this value and an empty argument list.
10814         return toISO.call(O);
10815 
10816         // NOTE 1 The argument is ignored.
10817 
10818         // NOTE 2 The toJSON function is intentionally generic; it does not
10819         // require that its this value be a Date object. Therefore, it can be
10820         // transferred to other kinds of objects for use as a method. However,
10821         // it does require that any such object have a toISOString method. An
10822         // object is free to use the argument key to filter its
10823         // stringification.
10824     };
10825 }

10827 // ES5 15.9.4.2
10828 // http://es5.github.com/#x15.9.4.2
10829 // based on work shared by Daniel Friesen (dantman)
10830 // http://gist.github.com/303249
10831 var supportsExtendedYears = Date.parse('+033658-09-27T01:46:40.000Z') === 1e15;
10832 var acceptsInvalidDates = !isNaN(Date.parse('2012-04-04T24:00:00.500Z')) || !isNaN(Date.parse('2012-11-31T23:59:59.000Z')) || !isNaN(Date.parse('2012-12-31T23:59:60.000Z'));
10833 var doesNotParseY2KNewYear = isNaN(Date.parse('2000-01-01T00:00:00.000Z'));
10834 if (doesNotParseY2KNewYear || acceptsInvalidDates || !supportsExtendedYears) {
10835     // XXX global assignment won't work in embeddings that use
10836     // an alternate object for the context.
10837     /* global Date: true */
10838     /* eslint-disable no-undef */
10839     var maxSafeUnsigned32Bit = Math.pow(2, 31) - 1;
10840     var hasSafariSignedIntBug = isActualNaN(new Date(1970, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, maxSafeUnsigned32Bit + 1).getTime());
10841     /* eslint-disable no-implicit-globals */
10842     Date = (function (NativeDate) {
10843     /* eslint-enable no-implicit-globals */
10844     /* eslint-enable no-undef */
10845         // Date.length === 7
10846         var DateShim = function Date(Y, M, D, h, m, s, ms) {
10847             var length = arguments.length;
10848             var date;
10849             if (this instanceof NativeDate) {
10850                 var seconds = s;
10851                 var millis = ms;
10852                 if (hasSafariSignedIntBug && length >= 7 && ms > maxSafeUnsigned32Bit) {
10853                     // work around a Safari 8/9 bug where it treats the seconds as signed
10854                     var msToShift = Math.floor(ms / maxSafeUnsigned32Bit) * maxSafeUnsigned32Bit;
10855                     var sToShift = Math.floor(msToShift / 1e3);
10856                     seconds += sToShift;
10857                     millis -= sToShift * 1e3;
10858                 }
10859                 date = length === 1 && $String(Y) === Y ? // isString(Y)
10860                     // We explicitly pass it through parse:
10861                     new NativeDate(DateShim.parse(Y)) :
10862                     // We have to manually make calls depending on argument
10863                     // length here
10864                     length >= 7 ? new NativeDate(Y, M, D, h, m, seconds, millis) :
10865                     length >= 6 ? new NativeDate(Y, M, D, h, m, seconds) :
10866                     length >= 5 ? new NativeDate(Y, M, D, h, m) :
10867                     length >= 4 ? new NativeDate(Y, M, D, h) :
10868                     length >= 3 ? new NativeDate(Y, M, D) :
10869                     length >= 2 ? new NativeDate(Y, M) :
10870                     length >= 1 ? new NativeDate(Y instanceof NativeDate ? +Y : Y) :
10871                                   new NativeDate();
10872             } else {
10873                 date = NativeDate.apply(this, arguments);
10874             }
10875             if (!isPrimitive(date)) {
10876               // Prevent mixups with unfixed Date object
10877               defineProperties(date, { constructor: DateShim }, true);
10878             }
10879             return date;
10880         };
10881 
10882         // 15.9.1.15 Date Time String Format.
10883         var isoDateExpression = new RegExp('^' +
10884             '(\\d{4}|[+-]\\d{6})' + // four-digit year capture or sign +
10885                                       // 6-digit extended year
10886             '(?:-(\\d{2})' + // optional month capture
10887             '(?:-(\\d{2})' + // optional day capture
10888             '(?:' + // capture hours:minutes:seconds.milliseconds
10889                 'T(\\d{2})' + // hours capture
10890                 ':(\\d{2})' + // minutes capture
10891                 '(?:' + // optional :seconds.milliseconds
10892                     ':(\\d{2})' + // seconds capture
10893                     '(?:(\\.\\d{1,}))?' + // milliseconds capture
10894                 ')?' +
10895             '(' + // capture UTC offset component
10896                 'Z|' + // UTC capture
10897                 '(?:' + // offset specifier +/-hours:minutes
10898                     '([-+])' + // sign capture
10899                     '(\\d{2})' + // hours offset capture
10900                     ':(\\d{2})' + // minutes offset capture
10901                 ')' +
10902             ')?)?)?)?' +
10903         '$');
10904 
10905         var months = [0, 31, 59, 90, 120, 151, 181, 212, 243, 273, 304, 334, 365];
10906 
10907         var dayFromMonth = function dayFromMonth(year, month) {
10908             var t = month > 1 ? 1 : 0;
10909             return (
10910                 months[month] +
10911                 Math.floor((year - 1969 + t) / 4) -
10912                 Math.floor((year - 1901 + t) / 100) +
10913                 Math.floor((year - 1601 + t) / 400) +
10914                 365 * (year - 1970)
10915             );
10916         };
10917 
10918         var toUTC = function toUTC(t) {
10919             var s = 0;
10920             var ms = t;
10921             if (hasSafariSignedIntBug && ms > maxSafeUnsigned32Bit) {
10922                 // work around a Safari 8/9 bug where it treats the seconds as signed
10923                 var msToShift = Math.floor(ms / maxSafeUnsigned32Bit) * maxSafeUnsigned32Bit;
10924                 var sToShift = Math.floor(msToShift / 1e3);
10925                 s += sToShift;
10926                 ms -= sToShift * 1e3;
10927             }
10928             return $Number(new NativeDate(1970, 0, 1, 0, 0, s, ms));
10929         };
10930 
10931         // Copy any custom methods a 3rd party library may have added
10932         for (var key in NativeDate) {
10933             if (owns(NativeDate, key)) {
10934                 DateShim[key] = NativeDate[key];
10935             }
10936         }
10937 
10938         // Copy "native" methods explicitly; they may be non-enumerable
10939         defineProperties(DateShim, {
10940             now: NativeDate.now,
10941             UTC: NativeDate.UTC
10942         }, true);
10943         DateShim.prototype = NativeDate.prototype;
10944         defineProperties(DateShim.prototype, {
10945             constructor: DateShim
10946         }, true);
10947 
10948         // Upgrade Date.parse to handle simplified ISO 8601 strings
10949         var parseShim = function parse(string) {
10950             var match = isoDateExpression.exec(string);
10951             if (match) {
10952                 // parse months, days, hours, minutes, seconds, and milliseconds
10953                 // provide default values if necessary
10954                 // parse the UTC offset component
10955                 var year = $Number(match[1]),
10956                     month = $Number(match[2] || 1) - 1,
10957                     day = $Number(match[3] || 1) - 1,
10958                     hour = $Number(match[4] || 0),
10959                     minute = $Number(match[5] || 0),
10960                     second = $Number(match[6] || 0),
10961                     millisecond = Math.floor($Number(match[7] || 0) * 1000),
10962                     // When time zone is missed, local offset should be used
10963                     // (ES 5.1 bug)
10964                     // see https://bugs.ecmascript.org/show_bug.cgi?id=112
10965                     isLocalTime = Boolean(match[4] && !match[8]),
10966                     signOffset = match[9] === '-' ? 1 : -1,
10967                     hourOffset = $Number(match[10] || 0),
10968                     minuteOffset = $Number(match[11] || 0),
10969                     result;
10970                 var hasMinutesOrSecondsOrMilliseconds = minute > 0 || second > 0 || millisecond > 0;
10971                 if (
10972                     hour < (hasMinutesOrSecondsOrMilliseconds ? 24 : 25) &&
10973                     minute < 60 && second < 60 && millisecond < 1000 &&
10974                     month > -1 && month < 12 && hourOffset < 24 &&
10975                     minuteOffset < 60 && // detect invalid offsets
10976                     day > -1 &&
10977                     day < (dayFromMonth(year, month + 1) - dayFromMonth(year, month))
10978                 ) {
10979                     result = (
10980                         (dayFromMonth(year, month) + day) * 24 +
10981                         hour +
10982                         hourOffset * signOffset
10983                     ) * 60;
10984                     result = (
10985                         (result + minute + minuteOffset * signOffset) * 60 +
10986                         second
10987                     ) * 1000 + millisecond;
10988                     if (isLocalTime) {
10989                         result = toUTC(result);
10990                     }
10991                     if (-8.64e15 <= result && result <= 8.64e15) {
10992                         return result;
10993                     }
10994                 }
10995                 return NaN;
10996             }
10997             return NativeDate.parse.apply(this, arguments);
10998         };
10999         defineProperties(DateShim, { parse: parseShim });
11000 
11001         return DateShim;
11002     }(Date));
11003     /* global Date: false */
11004 }

11021 var hasToFixedBugs = NumberPrototype.toFixed && (
11022   (0.00008).toFixed(3) !== '0.000' ||
11023   (0.9).toFixed(0) !== '1' ||
11024   (1.255).toFixed(2) !== '1.25' ||
11025   (1000000000000000128).toFixed(0) !== '1000000000000000128'

11027 
11028 var toFixedHelpers = {
11029   base: 1e7,
11030   size: 6,
11031   data: [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0],
11032   multiply: function multiply(n, c) {
11033       var i = -1;
11034       var c2 = c;
11035       while (++i < toFixedHelpers.size) {
11036           c2 += n * toFixedHelpers.data[i];
11037           toFixedHelpers.data[i] = c2 % toFixedHelpers.base;
11038           c2 = Math.floor(c2 / toFixedHelpers.base);
11039       }
11040   },
11041   divide: function divide(n) {
11042       var i = toFixedHelpers.size;
11043       var c = 0;
11044       while (--i >= 0) {
11045           c += toFixedHelpers.data[i];
11046           toFixedHelpers.data[i] = Math.floor(c / n);
11047           c = (c % n) * toFixedHelpers.base;
11048       }
11049   },
11050   numToString: function numToString() {
11051       var i = toFixedHelpers.size;
11052       var s = '';
11053       while (--i >= 0) {
11054           if (s !== '' || i === 0 || toFixedHelpers.data[i] !== 0) {
11055               var t = $String(toFixedHelpers.data[i]);
11056               if (s === '') {
11057                   s = t;
11058               } else {
11059                   s += strSlice('0000000', 0, 7 - t.length) + t;
11060               }
11061           }
11062       }
11063       return s;
11064   },
11065   pow: function pow(x, n, acc) {
11066       return (n === 0 ? acc : (n % 2 === 1 ? pow(x, n - 1, acc * x) : pow(x * x, n / 2, acc)));
11067   },
11068   log: function log(x) {
11069       var n = 0;
11070       var x2 = x;
11071       while (x2 >= 4096) {
11072           n += 12;
11073           x2 /= 4096;
11074       }
11075       while (x2 >= 2) {
11076           n += 1;
11077           x2 /= 2;
11078       }
11079       return n;
11080   }
11081 };
11082 
11083 var toFixedShim = function toFixed(fractionDigits) {
11084     var f, x, s, m, e, z, j, k;
11085 
11086     // Test for NaN and round fractionDigits down
11087     f = $Number(fractionDigits);
11088     f = isActualNaN(f) ? 0 : Math.floor(f);
11089 
11090     if (f < 0 || f > 20) {
11091         throw new RangeError('Number.toFixed called with invalid number of decimals');
11092     }
11093 
11094     x = $Number(this);
11095 
11096     if (isActualNaN(x)) {
11097         return 'NaN';
11098     }
11099 
11100     // If it is too big or small, return the string value of the number
11101     if (x <= -1e21 || x >= 1e21) {
11102         return $String(x);
11103     }
11104 
11105     s = '';
11106 
11107     if (x < 0) {
11108         s = '-';
11109         x = -x;
11110     }
11111 
11112     m = '0';
11113 
11114     if (x > 1e-21) {
11115         // 1e-21 < x < 1e21
11116         // -70 < log2(x) < 70
11117         e = toFixedHelpers.log(x * toFixedHelpers.pow(2, 69, 1)) - 69;
11118         z = (e < 0 ? x * toFixedHelpers.pow(2, -e, 1) : x / toFixedHelpers.pow(2, e, 1));
11119         z *= 0x10000000000000; // Math.pow(2, 52);
11120         e = 52 - e;
11121 
11122         // -18 < e < 122
11123         // x = z / 2 ^ e
11124         if (e > 0) {
11125             toFixedHelpers.multiply(0, z);
11126             j = f;
11127 
11128             while (j >= 7) {
11129                 toFixedHelpers.multiply(1e7, 0);
11130                 j -= 7;
11131             }
11132 
11133             toFixedHelpers.multiply(toFixedHelpers.pow(10, j, 1), 0);
11134             j = e - 1;
11135 
11136             while (j >= 23) {
11137                 toFixedHelpers.divide(1 << 23);
11138                 j -= 23;
11139             }
11140 
11141             toFixedHelpers.divide(1 << j);
11142             toFixedHelpers.multiply(1, 1);
11143             toFixedHelpers.divide(2);
11144             m = toFixedHelpers.numToString();
11145         } else {
11146             toFixedHelpers.multiply(0, z);
11147             toFixedHelpers.multiply(1 << (-e), 0);
11148             m = toFixedHelpers.numToString() + strSlice('0.00000000000000000000', 2, 2 + f);
11149         }
11150     }
11151 
11152     if (f > 0) {
11153         k = m.length;
11154 
11155         if (k <= f) {
11156             m = s + strSlice('0.0000000000000000000', 0, f - k + 2) + m;
11157         } else {
11158             m = s + strSlice(m, 0, k - f) + '.' + strSlice(m, k - f);
11159         }
11160     } else {
11161         m = s + m;
11162     }
11163 
11164     return m;
11165 };
11166 defineProperties(NumberPrototype, { toFixed: toFixedShim }, hasToFixedBugs);

11190 // [bugfix, IE lt 9, firefox 4, Konqueror, Opera, obscure browsers]
11191 // Many browsers do not split properly with regular expressions or they
11192 // do not perform the split correctly under obscure conditions.
11193 // See http://blog.stevenlevithan.com/archives/cross-browser-split
11194 // I've tested in many browsers and this seems to cover the deviant ones:
11195 //    'ab'.split(/(?:ab)*/) should be ["", ""], not [""]
11196 //    '.'.split(/(.?)(.?)/) should be ["", ".", "", ""], not ["", ""]
11197 //    'tesst'.split(/(s)*/) should be ["t", undefined, "e", "s", "t"], not
11198 //       [undefined, "t", undefined, "e", ...]
11199 //    ''.split(/.?/) should be [], not [""]
11200 //    '.'.split(/()()/) should be ["."], not ["", "", "."]

11203     'ab'.split(/(?:ab)*/).length !== 2 ||
11204     '.'.split(/(.?)(.?)/).length !== 4 ||

11206     'test'.split(/(?:)/, -1).length !== 4 ||
11207     ''.split(/.?/).length ||

11211         var compliantExecNpcg = typeof (/()??/).exec('')[1] === 'undefined'; // NPCG: nonparticipating capturing group
11212         var maxSafe32BitInt = Math.pow(2, 32) - 1;

11214         StringPrototype.split = function (separator, limit) {
11215             var string = String(this);
11216             if (typeof separator === 'undefined' && limit === 0) {
11217                 return [];
11218             }
11219 
11220             // If `separator` is not a regex, use native split
11221             if (!isRegex(separator)) {
11222                 return strSplit(this, separator, limit);
11223             }
11224 
11225             var output = [];
11226             var flags = (separator.ignoreCase ? 'i' : '') +
11227                         (separator.multiline ? 'm' : '') +
11228                         (separator.unicode ? 'u' : '') + // in ES6
11229                         (separator.sticky ? 'y' : ''), // Firefox 3+ and ES6
11230                 lastLastIndex = 0,
11231                 // Make `global` and avoid `lastIndex` issues by working with a copy
11232                 separator2, match, lastIndex, lastLength;
11233             var separatorCopy = new RegExp(separator.source, flags + 'g');
11234             if (!compliantExecNpcg) {
11235                 // Doesn't need flags gy, but they don't hurt
11236                 separator2 = new RegExp('^' + separatorCopy.source + '$(?!\\s)', flags);
11237             }
11238             /* Values for `limit`, per the spec:
11239              * If undefined: 4294967295 // maxSafe32BitInt
11240              * If 0, Infinity, or NaN: 0
11241              * If positive number: limit = Math.floor(limit); if (limit > 4294967295) limit -= 4294967296;
11242              * If negative number: 4294967296 - Math.floor(Math.abs(limit))
11243              * If other: Type-convert, then use the above rules
11244              */
11245             var splitLimit = typeof limit === 'undefined' ? maxSafe32BitInt : ES.ToUint32(limit);
11246             match = separatorCopy.exec(string);
11247             while (match) {
11248                 // `separatorCopy.lastIndex` is not reliable cross-browser
11249                 lastIndex = match.index + match[0].length;
11250                 if (lastIndex > lastLastIndex) {
11251                     pushCall(output, strSlice(string, lastLastIndex, match.index));
11252                     // Fix browsers whose `exec` methods don't consistently return `undefined` for
11253                     // nonparticipating capturing groups
11254                     if (!compliantExecNpcg && match.length > 1) {
11255                         /* eslint-disable no-loop-func */
11256                         match[0].replace(separator2, function () {
11257                             for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length - 2; i++) {
11258                                 if (typeof arguments[i] === 'undefined') {
11259                                     match[i] = void 0;
11260                                 }
11261                             }
11262                         });
11263                         /* eslint-enable no-loop-func */
11264                     }
11265                     if (match.length > 1 && match.index < string.length) {
11266                         array_push.apply(output, arraySlice(match, 1));
11267                     }
11268                     lastLength = match[0].length;
11269                     lastLastIndex = lastIndex;
11270                     if (output.length >= splitLimit) {
11271                         break;
11272                     }
11273                 }
11274                 if (separatorCopy.lastIndex === match.index) {
11275                     separatorCopy.lastIndex++; // Avoid an infinite loop
11276                 }
11277                 match = separatorCopy.exec(string);
11278             }
11279             if (lastLastIndex === string.length) {
11280                 if (lastLength || !separatorCopy.test('')) {
11281                     pushCall(output, '');
11282                 }
11283             } else {
11284                 pushCall(output, strSlice(string, lastLastIndex));
11285             }
11286             return output.length > splitLimit ? arraySlice(output, 0, splitLimit) : output;
11287         };
11288     }());

11638     return new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
11639       reader.onload = function() {
11640         resolve(reader.result)
11641       }
11642       reader.onerror = function() {
11643         reject(reader.error)
11644       }
11645     })
11646   }
11647 
11648   function readBlobAsArrayBuffer(blob) {
11649     var reader = new FileReader()
11650     reader.readAsArrayBuffer(blob)
11651     return fileReaderReady(reader)
11652   }
11653 
11654   function readBlobAsText(blob) {
11655     var reader = new FileReader()
11656     reader.readAsText(blob)
11657     return fileReaderReady(reader)
11658   }
11659 
11660   function Body() {
11661     this.bodyUsed = false
11662 
11663     this._initBody = function(body) {
11664       this._bodyInit = body
11665       if (typeof body === 'string') {
11666         this._bodyText = body
11667       } else if (support.blob && Blob.prototype.isPrototypeOf(body)) {
11668         this._bodyBlob = body
11669       } else if (support.formData && FormData.prototype.isPrototypeOf(body)) {
11670         this._bodyFormData = body
11671       } else if (support.searchParams && URLSearchParams.prototype.isPrototypeOf(body)) {
11672         this._bodyText = body.toString()
11673       } else if (!body) {
11674         this._bodyText = ''
11675       } else if (support.arrayBuffer && ArrayBuffer.prototype.isPrototypeOf(body)) {
11676         // Only support ArrayBuffers for POST method.
11677         // Receiving ArrayBuffers happens via Blobs, instead.
11678       } else {
11679         throw new Error('unsupported BodyInit type')
11680       }
11681 
11682       if (!this.headers.get('content-type')) {
11683         if (typeof body === 'string') {
11684           this.headers.set('content-type', 'text/plain;charset=UTF-8')
11685         } else if (this._bodyBlob && this._bodyBlob.type) {
11686           this.headers.set('content-type', this._bodyBlob.type)
11687         } else if (support.searchParams && URLSearchParams.prototype.isPrototypeOf(body)) {
11688           this.headers.set('content-type', 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded;charset=UTF-8')
11689         }
11690       }
11691     }
11692 
11693     if (support.blob) {
11694       this.blob = function() {
11695         var rejected = consumed(this)
11696         if (rejected) {
11697           return rejected
11698         }
11699 
11700         if (this._bodyBlob) {
11701           return Promise.resolve(this._bodyBlob)
11702         } else if (this._bodyFormData) {
11703           throw new Error('could not read FormData body as blob')
11704         } else {
11705           return Promise.resolve(new Blob([this._bodyText]))
11706         }
11707       }
11708 
11709       this.arrayBuffer = function() {
11710         return this.blob().then(readBlobAsArrayBuffer)
11711       }
11712 
11713       this.text = function() {
11714         var rejected = consumed(this)
11715         if (rejected) {
11716           return rejected
11717         }
11718 
11719         if (this._bodyBlob) {
11720           return readBlobAsText(this._bodyBlob)
11721         } else if (this._bodyFormData) {
11722           throw new Error('could not read FormData body as text')
11723         } else {
11724           return Promise.resolve(this._bodyText)
11725         }
11726       }
11727     } else {
11728       this.text = function() {
11729         var rejected = consumed(this)
11730         return rejected ? rejected : Promise.resolve(this._bodyText)
11731       }
11732     }
11733 
11734     if (support.formData) {
11735       this.formData = function() {
11736         return this.text().then(decode)
11737       }
11738     }
11739 
11740     this.json = function() {
11741       return this.text().then(JSON.parse)
11742     }
11743 
11744     return this
11745   }

11747   // HTTP methods whose capitalization should be normalized
11748   var methods = ['DELETE', 'GET', 'HEAD', 'OPTIONS', 'POST', 'PUT']
11749 
11750   function normalizeMethod(method) {
11751     var upcased = method.toUpperCase()
11752     return (methods.indexOf(upcased) > -1) ? upcased : method
11753   }
11754 
11755   function Request(input, options) {
11756     options = options || {}
11757     var body = options.body
11758     if (Request.prototype.isPrototypeOf(input)) {
11759       if (input.bodyUsed) {
11760         throw new TypeError('Already read')
11761       }
11762       this.url = input.url
11763       this.credentials = input.credentials
11764       if (!options.headers) {
11765         this.headers = new Headers(input.headers)
11766       }
11767       this.method = input.method
11768       this.mode = input.mode
11769       if (!body) {
11770         body = input._bodyInit
11771         input.bodyUsed = true
11772       }
11773     } else {
11774       this.url = input
11775     }
11776 
11777     this.credentials = options.credentials || this.credentials || 'omit'
11778     if (options.headers || !this.headers) {
11779       this.headers = new Headers(options.headers)
11780     }
11781     this.method = normalizeMethod(options.method || this.method || 'GET')
11782     this.mode = options.mode || this.mode || null
11783     this.referrer = null
11784 
11785     if ((this.method === 'GET' || this.method === 'HEAD') && body) {
11786       throw new TypeError('Body not allowed for GET or HEAD requests')
11787     }
11788     this._initBody(body)
11789   }
11790 
11791   Request.prototype.clone = function() {
11792     return new Request(this)
11793   }
11794 
11795   function decode(body) {
11796     var form = new FormData()
11797     body.trim().split('&').forEach(function(bytes) {
11798       if (bytes) {
11799         var split = bytes.split('=')
11800         var name = split.shift().replace(/\+/g, ' ')
11801         var value = split.join('=').replace(/\+/g, ' ')
11802         form.append(decodeURIComponent(name), decodeURIComponent(value))
11803       }
11804     })
11805     return form
11806   }
11807 
11808   function headers(xhr) {
11809     var head = new Headers()
11810     var pairs = (xhr.getAllResponseHeaders() || '').trim().split('\n')
11811     pairs.forEach(function(header) {
11812       var split = header.trim().split(':')
11813       var key = split.shift().trim()
11814       var value = split.join(':').trim()
11815       head.append(key, value)
11816     })
11817     return head
11818   }
11819 
11820   Body.call(Request.prototype)
11821 
11822   function Response(bodyInit, options) {
11823     if (!options) {
11824       options = {}
11825     }
11826 
11827     this.type = 'default'
11828     this.status = options.status
11829     this.ok = this.status >= 200 && this.status < 300
11830     this.statusText = options.statusText
11831     this.headers = options.headers instanceof Headers ? options.headers : new Headers(options.headers)
11832     this.url = options.url || ''
11833     this._initBody(bodyInit)
11834   }
11835 
11836   Body.call(Response.prototype)
11837 
11838   Response.prototype.clone = function() {
11839     return new Response(this._bodyInit, {
11840       status: this.status,
11841       statusText: this.statusText,
11842       headers: new Headers(this.headers),
11843       url: this.url
11844     })
11845   }
11846 
11847   Response.error = function() {
11848     var response = new Response(null, {status: 0, statusText: ''})
11849     response.type = 'error'
11850     return response
11851   }
11852 
11853   var redirectStatuses = [301, 302, 303, 307, 308]
11854 
11855   Response.redirect = function(url, status) {
11856     if (redirectStatuses.indexOf(status) === -1) {
11857       throw new RangeError('Invalid status code')
11858     }
11859 
11860     return new Response(null, {status: status, headers: {location: url}})
11861   }
11862 
11863   self.Headers = Headers
11864   self.Request = Request
11865   self.Response = Response
11866 
11867   self.fetch = function(input, init) {
11868     return new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
11869       var request
11870       if (Request.prototype.isPrototypeOf(input) && !init) {
11871         request = input
11872       } else {
11873         request = new Request(input, init)
11874       }
11875 
11876       var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest()
11877 
11878       function responseURL() {
11879         if ('responseURL' in xhr) {
11880           return xhr.responseURL
11881         }
11882 
11883         // Avoid security warnings on getResponseHeader when not allowed by CORS
11884         if (/^X-Request-URL:/m.test(xhr.getAllResponseHeaders())) {
11885           return xhr.getResponseHeader('X-Request-URL')
11886         }
11887 
11888         return
11889       }
11890 
11891       xhr.onload = function() {
11892         var options = {
11893           status: xhr.status,
11894           statusText: xhr.statusText,
11895           headers: headers(xhr),
11896           url: responseURL()
11897         }
11898         var body = 'response' in xhr ? xhr.response : xhr.responseText
11899         resolve(new Response(body, options))
11900       }
11901 
11902       xhr.onerror = function() {
11903         reject(new TypeError('Network request failed'))
11904       }
11905 
11906       xhr.ontimeout = function() {
11907         reject(new TypeError('Network request failed'))
11908       }
11909 
11910       xhr.open(request.method, request.url, true)
11911 
11912       if (request.credentials === 'include') {
11913         xhr.withCredentials = true
11914       }
11915 
11916       if ('responseType' in xhr && support.blob) {
11917         xhr.responseType = 'blob'
11918       }
11919 
11920       request.headers.forEach(function(value, name) {
11921         xhr.setRequestHeader(name, value)
11922       })
11923 
11924       xhr.send(typeof request._bodyInit === 'undefined' ? null : request._bodyInit)
11925     })
11926   }
11927   self.fetch.polyfill = true
11928 })(typeof self !== 'undefined' ? self : this);
